FORMAT: 1A
HOST: https://demo.mystock.cz/

# mySTOCK


## mySTOCK API description

API supports communication in JSON format. The URL for calling API requests is specific for each customer. The API uses username and password authorization and authentication (HTTP Header Basic Authentication). 
Result of each call always contains two sections - <b>data</b> and <b>errors</b>.

When processing the response, the client shall first detect what response status code was received. If mySTOCK API responds to your request with a 200 code, it is not necessary to explore the errors part of the response. 
The unknown record is returned with a 404 code etc. These responses have the errors field filled in, where you can find detailed info about the error.

The data sent from mySTOCK API are first transferred to the interface database, from where they are subsequently transferred to the WMS database. 
The validity of transferred data in the interface database is limited, after a certain amount of time the data from this database may be deleted.


## Error format

+ errorText: `Logical key is not unique` (string) - Error text
+ errorType: `5` (number) - Error type (see below)
+ internalRecordId: `BF961B2D-3019-4872-95C4-F44E9F5A108C` (string) - If there is an attempt to create a record that already exists in the database, mySTOCK API fills in the element "internalRecordId" with the ID that was generated when the original record was created.
+ propertyName: `items.measurementUnitCode` (string) - Optional name of invalid property
+ recordId: `1` (string) - If header is faulted then 0, else order of faulted item.
+ recordType: `partner` (string) - Type of faulted record
+ sourceId: `KV0012` (string) - If there is an attempt to create a record that already exists in the database, mySTOCK API fills in the element "sourceId" with the logical key from the ERP that was used to create the original record (either unique code of the record or value from the element "extIsId").
+ extensionData.path: `orderIncoming/relations/OrderInHeader/OrderInPackagingTypeGroup` (string) - Path to the relational table.
+ extensionData.relationId: `DB2B98FC-0593-4676-9965-C91725E21D2E` (string) - If an attempt is made to create a record in the relational table that already exists in the database, mySTOCK API will fill in the element extensionData.relationId with the ID that was generated during the creation of the original record.
+ extensionData.relationSourceId: `0702240900` (string) - If there is an attempt to create a record in the relational table that already exists in the database, mySTOCK API will fill in the element extensionData.relationSourceId with the logical key from the ERP that was used to create the original record (either the unique code of the record or the value from the extIsId element).

### Error types

+ 1 - Value is NULL
+ 2 - Value is not specified
+ 3 - Invalid value - e.g. id of nonexisting record
+ 4 - Other specific error
+ 5 - Value is not unique
+ 6 - Update of record is forbidden
+ 7 - Value overflow e.g. string is too long
+ 100 - Internal server error. Unique record id is set in recordId
+ 101 - API limit exceeded
+ 102 - Concurrent request wait timeout

## Get data result [GET]

Each get data GET request returns required data in <b>data/result</b> section.

Response HTTP Status is 200 when succeeded.

## Insert result [POST]

Each insert POST request returns list of generated id in <b>data/ids</b> section:

+ id: `2949C3DE-F4AC-4FF7-8AF8-48EBED3EA7A6` - Unique identifier of the record, the ID is always generated by the WMS and is sent back to the ERP. The ID is later used in additional web services (e.g. an ID of the product is required in the order incoming web service) or in the events exported by the WMS.
+ recordId: `0` - Record order if more than one record is inserted 
+ type: `product` - Record type

Response HTTP Status is 201 when succeeded.

## Update result [PUT]

Each update PUT request returns only confirmation text in <b>data</b> section when succesfull or list of errors in <b>errors</b> section when failed.

Only records that are active in WMS can be updated.

Response HTTP Status is 200 when succeeded. 

## Delete result [DELETE]

Each delete DELETE request returns only confirmation text in <b>data</b> section when succesfull or list of errors in <b>errors</b> section when failed.

Response HTTP Status is 200 when succeeded.

## Exporting events (webhook) [POST]

When some defined action occurs in the WMS, mySTOCK generates an event that can be sent to your service. Your service must meet the following conditions:
+ Use HTTPS with Basic authentication.
+ Receive POST request on URI /V1/event - the events exported from the WMS are sent to the URL address you provide which must end with the suffix „/V1/event“ (e.g. "https://demo.mystock.cz/V1/event").
+ The HTTP status of your server’s response to the request must be `200` - this response must contain id of the record created by the ERP in <b>data</b> section, <b>errors</b> section must be blank. Other HTTP statuses are considered as fault.
+ If some error occurs when receiving an event request, return response `400` with error message in <b>errors</b> section and no id in <b>data</b> section.
+ The WMS needs to receive a response for all the sent events – response 200 confirms successful receipt of the event sent from the WMS to the ERP. If the WMS does not receive any response from the ERP or the response is 400, the event is treated as not yet processed and the WMS will try to retransmit the event.
+ In the case of response 400, ERP has the option to send a message with "errorType" 8, which informs WMS that it should not try to send the event again.

Each event request contains unique eventId. When some problem occurs when sending an event to your service, the same event can be sent later with the same eventId - please check eventId in your service to avoid possible repetitive processing of the same event.

### Event types

Each type of event can contain specific subset of elements (see reference of single event types examples for details).
List of all currently supported event types:
+ 1 - Request to print from the ERP system
+ 2 - Request to print shipping label from the ERP system
+ 3 - Change of location or warehouse of the ERP system (caused by the change of location in the WMS)
+ 5 - Dispensing in the WMS
+ 6 - Receipt of product in the WMS
+ 7 - Completion of document processing in the WMS
+ 8 - Ready for loading
+ 11 - Change of the product's dimensions
+ 12 - Dispatch of a shipment from the warehouse
+ 14 - Product putaway
+ 15 - Completion of stocking up in WMS
+ 16 - Start of shipment generation
+ 17 - Start of picking of the shipment
+ 19 - Received/issued serial numbers
+ 20 - Document cancellation
+ 21 - Change of the delivery method
+ 22 - Export of atest date
+ 24 - Received carrier
+ 25 - Export of results from inventory check
+ 26 - Export of logistics units
+ 27 - Request to create a record in the ERP system
+ 28 - Incompletely picked document
+ 29 - Shipment status in carrier’s system
+ 30 - Dispensing of the product in the WMS (including logistics units)
+ 32 - Receipt of the manufactured product in the WMS
+ 33 - Export of inventory items price request
+ 34 - Insufficient quantity for allocation

