## Partner [/V1/partner/]

Base URI template that is used at the end of the URL when the web service is called: <b>/V1/partner/</b> (example: https://demo.mystock.cz/V1/partner/).

The web service has following elements:
+ code: `P0045` (string (150), required) - Partner code from the ERP - a unique identifier that cannot be changed over time, it is used to identify a partner in the WMS. The code is displayed to warehouse operators on mobile devices and is printed in reports.
+ extIsId: `1D15F666` (string(1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP that must be used when it is not possible to ensure that the value in the element "code" is unique. If the identification in the element "code" is unique, "extIsId" should not be filled in.
+ type: `3` (tinyint, required) - Supported partner types: 0 - Not specified, 1 - Customer, 2 - Supplier, 3 - Customer and supplier.
+ name: `Partner 45, a.s.` (string (150), required) - Name of the partner.
+ nameShort: `Par 45` (string (20)) - Short name of the partner, if the element is not filled in, the WMS uses first 20 characters from the partner's name as the short name.
+ companyRegistrationID: `ICO12345` (string (30)) - Partner's registration number. The registration number must be unique - if the same registration number is already used with different partner, the entry will not be imported into the WMS. Registration number cannot be longer than 15 characters and can contain only capital letters and numbers (no spaces are permitted).
+ active: `1` (tinyint) - Defines if the partner is active. Supported values: 0 - No, 1 - Yes. If no value is filled in, the partner is inserted as active.
+ mergeShipping: `1` (tinyint) - Determines whether it is possible to combine the partner's order incoming together with other orders incoming with the same place of delivery into one shipment. Supported values: 0 - No, 1 - Yes.
+ packingListRequired: `0` (tinyint) - Defines whether the packaging list should be printed during dispatch. Supported values: 0 – Do not print, 1 - after import into WMS it is transformed to the value 30, 20 - Partial - for each logistics unit, 30 - For the order incoming - to the last logistics unit
+ deliveryNoteRequired: `0` (tinyint) - Defines whether the delivery note should be printed during dispatch. Supported values: 0 – Do not print, 1 - after import into WMS it is transformed to the value 30, 20 - Partial - for each logistics unit, 30 - For the order incoming - to the last logistics unit
+ invoiceRequired: `0` (tinyint) - Defines whether the invoice should be printed during dispatch. Supported values: 0 – Do not print, 1 - after import into WMS it is transformed to the value 30, 20 - Partial - for each logistics unit, 30 - For the order incoming - to the last logistics unit
+ outboundCheck: `10` (tinyint) - Mandatory outbound check. In the case of "Not specified", the outbound check is mandatory according to other conditions and settings (e.g. by order incoming, order incoming item, shipment, person who processed the document). Supported values: 0 - Not specified, 10 - Yes, 20 - No, 30 - Soft.
+ partyIdentification.street: `Novoveská 22` (string (100)) - Street.
+ partyIdentification.city: `Ostrava` (string (100)) - City.
+ partyIdentification.zip: `70900` (string (20)) - ZIP code.
+ partyIdentification.country: `CZ` (string (20), required) - Country code should be filled according to the ISO 3166-1 standard with alpha-2 codes (e.g. "CZ" for Czech Republic).
+ partyIdentification.email: `jan@novak.cz` (string (60)) - E-mail.
+ partyIdentification.phone: `+420558123456` (string (60)) - Phone number.
+ operatingUnits: Optional collection of partner's operating units. See chapter Partner's operating unit for the list of possible elements of the operating units.

### Create a Partner [POST /V1/partner/]

When a partner is created,operating unit can be created either alongside the partner (see the section "operatingUnits" in the example) or later with separate service (see the header "Partner's operating unit").

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "code": "P0045",
            "extIsId": "1D15F666",
            "type": 3,
            "name": "Partner 45, a.s.",
            "nameShort": "Par 45",
            "companyRegistrationID": "ICO12345",
            "active": 1,
            "mergeShipping": 1,
            "packingListRequired": 0,
            "deliveryNoteRequired": 0,
            "invoiceRequired": 0,
            "outboundCheck": 10,
            "partyIdentification": {
                "street": "Novoveská 22",
                "city": "Ostrava",
                "zip": "70900",
                "country": "CZ",
                "email": "jan@novak.cz",
                "phone": "+420558123456"
            },
            "operatingUnits": [
                {
                    "code": "PJ001",
                    "extIsId": "33A50301",
                    "type": 1,
                    "name": "Provozní jednotka 1",
                    "partyIdentification": {
                        "city": "Ostrava",
                        "country": "CZ",
                        "email": "a@a.cz",
                        "phone": "+420558123456",
                        "street": "Novoveská",
                        "zip": "70900"
                    }
                }
            ]
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
        "data": 
            {
            "ids": [
                {
                    "id": "4D63AD01-B5F8-4B1F-9F4B-863C135926C0",
                    "recordId": "1",
                    "sourceId": "1D15F666",
                    "type": "partner"
                },
                 {
                    "id": "1A672B37-B674-4F14-A13F-C82EAF53BF15",
                    "recordId": "1",
                    "sourceId": "33A50301",
                    "type": "partnerOperatingUnit"
                }
            ]
            },
        "errors": []
        }
        
+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
        "data": null,
        "errors": [
            {
                "errorText": "Logical key is not unique",
                "errorType": 5,
                "internalRecordId": "FAEA266F-1FC6-4A39-A848-748038AB3A20",
                "propertyName": "code",
                "recordId": "1",
                "recordType": "partner",
                "sourceId": "1D15F666"
            }
            ]
        }

### Update a Partner [PUT /V1/partner/{partnerId}]
In the update web service, it is always necessary to send a unique identification of the changed record (ID) in the URL. The body of the update web service must always contain all the mandatory elements (see below), other elements should be filled in only when there is need to change the information they contain (e.g. if you only need to change partner's name, all the other optional elements should remain null).

Only partner information may be updated using this web service, if you want to update partner's operating unit, use the corresponding web service.

If one of the updated values is filled in incorrectly and the validation procedure reports an error, the system will cancel the whole update - none of the changed values will be updated.

List of elements that may be updated:
+ type: `3` (tinyint)
+ name: `Partner 45, a.s.` (string (150))
+ nameShort: `Par 45` (string (20))
+ companyRegistrationID: `ICO12345` (string (30))
+ active: `1` (tinyint)
+ mergeShipping: `1` (tinyint)
+ packingListRequired: `0` (tinyint)
+ deliveryNoteRequired: `0` (tinyint)
+ invoiceRequired: `0` (tinyint)
+ outboundCheck: `10` (tinyint)
+ partyIdentification.street: `Novoveská 22` (string (100))
+ partyIdentification.city: `Ostrava` (string (100))
+ partyIdentification.zip: `70900` (string (20))
+ partyIdentification.country: `CZ` (string (20))
+ partyIdentification.email: `jan@novak.cz` (string (60))
+ partyIdentification.phone: `+420558123456` (string (60))

+ Parameters
    + partnerId: `4D63AD01-B5F8-4B1F-9F4B-863C135926C0` (string) - A unique identifier of the partner you want to update.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "type": 3,
            "name": "Partner 45, a.s.",
            "nameShort": "Par 45",
            "companyRegistrationID": "ICO12345",
            "active": 1,
            "mergeShipping": 1,
            "packingListRequired": 0,
            "deliveryNoteRequired": 0,
            "invoiceRequired": 0,
            "outboundCheck": 10,
            "partyIdentification": {
                "street": "Novoveská 22",
                "city": "Ostrava",
                "zip": "70900",
                "country": "CZ",
                "email": "jan@novak.cz",
                "phone": "+420558123456"
            }  
        }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
        "data": "OK",
        "errors": []
        }
        
+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
        "data": null,
        "errors": [
            {
                "errorText": "Invalid entry",
                "errorType": 3,
                "internalRecordId": null,
                "propertyName": "partyIdentification.country",
                "recordId": "1",
                "recordType": "partner",
                "sourceId": "1D15F666"
            }
            ]
        }

## Partner's operating unit [/V1/partnerOperatingUnit/]

Base URI template that is used at the end of the URL when the web service is called: <b>/V1/partnerOperatingUnit/</b> (example: https://demo.mystock.cz/V1/partnerOperatingUnit/).

The web service has following elements:
+ code: `PJ002` (string (20), required) - Operating unit code from the ERP - a unique identifier that cannot be changed over time, it is used to identify partner's operating unit in the WMS. The code is displayed to warehouse operators on mobile devices and is printed in reports.
+ extIsId: `473E380B` (string(1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP that must be used when it is not possible to ensure that the value in the element "code" is unique. If the identification in the element "code" is unique, "extIsId" should not be filled in.
+ partnerId: `4D63AD01-B5F8-4B1F-9F4B-863C135926C0` (string (1024), required) - Unique identifier of the partner - the ID is generated during the creation of the partner via API.
+ type: `2` (tinyint, required) - Supported operating unit types: 0 - Not specified, 1 - Customer, 2 - Supplier, 3 - Customer and supplier.
+ name: `Provozní jednotka 2` (string (150), required) - Name of the operating unit.
+ partyIdentification.street: `Novoveská 22` (string (100)) - Street.
+ partyIdentification.city: `Ostrava` (string (100)) - City.
+ partyIdentification.zip: `70900` (string (20)) - ZIP code.
+ partyIdentification.country: `CZ` (string (20), required) - Country code should be filled according to the ISO 3166-1 standard with alpha-2 codes (e.g. "CZ" for Czech Republic).
+ partyIdentification.email: `jan@novak.cz` (string (60)) - E-mail.
+ partyIdentification.phone: `731123456` (string (60)) - Phone number.

### Create a Partner's operating unit[POST /V1/partnerOperatingUnit/]

Partner's operating unit can be created either alongside the partner by using the "Create a Partner" web service or after the partner is already created by using the "Create a Partner's operating unit" web service.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
        "code": "PJ002",
        "extIsId": "473E380B",
        "partnerId" : "4D63AD01-B5F8-4B1F-9F4B-863C135926C0",
        "type": 2,
        "name": "Provozní jednotka 2",
        "partyIdentification": {
            "street": "Novoveská 22",
            "city": "Ostrava",
            "zip": "70900",
            "country": "CZ",
            "email": "jan@novak.cz",
            "phone": "+420558123456"
            }    
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
        "data": 
            {
            "ids": [
                {
                    "id": "C68CE16E-42E1-4E5D-BE6C-BC8897FF6479",
                    "recordId": "1",
                    "sourceId": "473E380B",
                    "type": "partnerOperatingUnit"
                }
            ]
            },
        "errors": []
        }
        
+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
        "data": null,
        "errors": [
            {
                "errorText": "Invalid value",
                "errorType": 3,
                "internalRecordId": null,
                "propertyName": "partnerId",
                "recordId": "1",
                "recordType": "partnerOperatingUnit",
                "sourceId": "473E380B"
            }
            ]
        }

### Update a Partner's operating unit[PUT /V1/partnerOperatingUnit/{partnerOperatingUnitId}]

In the update web service, it is always necessary to send a unique identification of the changed record (ID) in the URL. The body of the update web service must always contain all the mandatory elements (see below), other elements should be filled in only when there is need to change the information they contain (e.g. if you only need to change operating unit's name, all the other optional elements should remain null).

If one of the updated values is filled in incorrectly and the validation procedure reports an error, the system will cancel the whole update - none of the changed values will be updated.

List of elements that may be updated:
+ partnerId: `4D63AD01-B5F8-4B1F-9F4B-863C135926C0` (string (1024), required) - The ID of the partner to which the operating unit belongs. It is not possible to change the partner ID within the update - if you want to assign the given operating unit to another partner, you must deactivate the operating unit for the original partner and create a new operating unit for the new partner.
+ type: `2` (tinyint)
+ name: `Provozní jednotka 2` (string (150))
+ partyIdentification.street: `Novoveská 22` (string (100))
+ partyIdentification.city: `Ostrava` (string (100))
+ partyIdentification.zip: `70900` (string (20))
+ partyIdentification.country: `CZ` (string (20))
+ partyIdentification.email: `jan@novak.cz` (string (60))
+ partyIdentification.phone: `731123456` (string (60))

+ Parameters
    + partnerOperatingUnitId: `C68CE16E-42E1-4E5D-BE6C-BC8897FF6479` (string) - A unique identifier of the partner's operating unit you want to update.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "partnerId": "4D63AD01-B5F8-4B1F-9F4B-863C135926C0",
            "type": 2,
            "name": "Provozní jednotka 2",
            "partyIdentification": {
                "street": "Novoveská 22",
                "city": "Ostrava",
                "zip": "70900",
                "country": "CZ",
                "email": "jan@novak.cz",
                "phone": "+420558123456"
            }
        }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
        "data": "OK",
        "errors": []
        }
        
+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
        "data": null,
        "errors": [
            {
                "errorText": "Invalid value",
                "errorType": 3,
                "internalRecordId": null,
                "propertyName": "partnerId",
                "recordId": "1",
                "recordType": "partnerOperatingUnit",
                "sourceId": "473E380B"
            }
            ]
        }

## Product [/V1/product/]

Base URI template that is used at the end of the URL when the web service is called: <b>/V1/product/</b> (example: https://demo.mystock.cz/V1/product/).

The web service has following elements:
+ productCode: `X415EA-EB037T` (string (150), required) - Unique product code from the ERP system. The code is displayed to warehouse operators on mobile devices and is printed in reports.
+ extIsId: `648DC0FF` (string(1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP that must be used when it is not possible to ensure that the value in the element "productCode" is unique. If the identification in the element "productCode" is unique, "extIsId" should not be filled in.
+ name: `Asus X415EA-EB037T Slate Grey` (string (255), required) - Name of the product.
+ nameShort: `Asus X415EA` (string (150), condition) - Short name of the product. The maximum length of the product's short name can vary as it is set in the WMS (it is usually set to 40 characters). The setting in the WMS also determines whether the value must be sent from an ERP system.
+ type: `0` (smallint, required) - Supported product types: 0 - Goods (basic product type which is used most often), 10 - Material, 20 - Packaging, 30 - Other without stock, 40 - Product (products manufactured in the warehouse), 50 - Set, 60 - Semi-finished product, 70 - Production in progress, 80 - Gift voucher, 90 - Fabric, 100 - Promotional material.
+ subtype: `0` (tinyint) - Supported product subtypes: 0 - Not specified, 10 - Carrier service, 20 - Supplementary product.
+ warehouseCode: `1001` (string(20)) - Warehouse code must be registered in the WMS (if the customer works with multiple warehouses registered in the WMS, it is sufficient to fill in only one warehouse code).
+ measurementUnitCode: `KS` (string (1024), required) - Basic unit of measurement in which the product is recorded on stock cards - the code is generated during the creation of the unit of measurement in the WMS.
+ weightGross: `10.5` (numeric (15,4)) - Gross weight of the product (in kilograms).
+ weightNett: `9.5` (numeric (15,4)) - Net weight of the product (in kilograms).
+ grossDimension.height: `2` (numeric (8,4)) - Gross height of the product (in meters).
+ grossDimension.width: `1.5` (numeric (8,4)) - Gross width of the product (in meters).
+ grossDimension.depth: `3.5` (numeric (8,4)) - Gross depth of the product (in meters).
+ grossDimension.volume: `10.5` (numeric (15,4)) - Gross volume of the product (in cubic meters).
+ pictureUrl: `www.mystock.cz/product.png` (string (255)) - URL path to the image of the product. If the URL contains backslash character, the backslash has to be doubled (e.g. a UNC path "\\\\192.168.55.3\\product\\377169719.jpg" has to be sent as "\\\\\\\\192.168.55.3\\\\product\\\\377169719.jpg" - this limitation is based on the JSON characteristics).
+ pictureData: `/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQEASABIAAD/4gxYSUNDX1BST0ZJTEUAAQEAAAxITG` (varbinary) - Binary data to convert to image in Base64.
+ expirationMandatory: `1` (tinyint) - Mandatory registration of the expiration date. Supported values: 0 - No, 1 - Yes.
+ expirationPeriod: `365` (integer, condition) - Total shelf life (expiration date) of the product in days. Mutually exclusive with element "expirationPeriodInMonth" - at any time only one of these two may be set. Permitted settings: 1) Both elements are undefined (null value), 2) Value of one element is set to 0 and the other element has any positive number.
+ expirationPeriodSupplier: `30` (integer) - Defines the minimum shelf life (in days) on receipt as specified by the supplier.
+ expirationPeriodInMonth: `12` (integer, condition) - Defines the product's shelf life in months. Mutually exclusive with element "expirationPeriod" (days) - at any time only one of these two may be set. Permitted settings: 1) Both elements are undefined (null value), 2) Value of one element is set to 0 and the other element has any positive number.
+ batches: `0` (tinyint) - Mandatory registration of batch numbers. Supported values: 0 - No, 1 - Yes.
+ variantMandatory: `0` (tinyint) - Mandatory registration of variants. Supported values: 0 - no, 1 - yes.
+ atestMandatory: `0` (tinyint) - Mandatory registration of atests. Supported values: 0 - no, 1 - yes.
+ serialNumbersRecords.inboundMandatory: `0` (tinyint) - Mandatory registration of serial numbers (inbound). Supported values: 0 - No, 1 - Yes.
+ serialNumbersRecords.outboundMandatory: `1` (tinyint) - Mandatory registration of serial numbers (outbound). Supported values: 0 - No, 1 - Yes.
+ manufacturerProductNumber: `BV373` (string (40)) - Product number defined by the manufacturer.
+ storeSeparately: `0` (tinyint) - Information on whether the product is to be stored separately. Supported values: 0 - No, 1 - Yes.
+ brandId: `BC9B92F8-71DE-449B-917C-4029E6CFA6C1` (string (1024)) - ID of the first brand of the product- the ID is generated within the web service for importing item lists.
+ brandId2: `90AD3F04-1489-4CC8-8FD4-3AEEE62379E7` (string (1024)) - ID of the second brand of the product - the ID is generated within the web service for importing item lists.
+ conversionMeasurementUnitCode: `M2` (string (1024)) - Conversion unit of measurement.
+ barcodes: Optional collection of product's barcodes. See chapter Product barcode for the list of possible elements of the barcodes.
+ handling equipments: Optional collection of product's handling equipments. See chapter Product handling equipment for the list of possible elements of the handling equipments.
+ groupId: `D959BB85-0F8F-44F5-AA2F-B028C8F69F38` (string (1024)) - ID of the product group - the ID is generated within the web service for importing product groups.
+ productLabelPrint: `0` (tinyint) - Setting which guides user in WMS to print product label (containing barcode) or stock card label while receiving product. Supported values: 0 - No, 1 - Yes.
+ productLabelPrintReceipt: `0` (tinyint) - Indicates whether a product label should be printed for this item upon receipt. Supported values: 0 - No, 1 - Yes.
+ primarySupplierId: `AFF2D206-09B5-4B09-A391-876B20502485` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the supplier - the ID is generated during the creation of the supplier via API. Supplier must be active in WMS.
+ description: `Description of the product` (string (32766)) - Optional description of the product.
+ commodityCode: `58475465` (string (14)) - Commodity code - customs tariff
+ countryCode: `CZ` (string (3)) - Country code
+ palletQuantity: `7` (numeric (15,4)) - Number of quantity per pallet.
+ salesCategoryId: `KAT` (string (1024), condition) - ID of the preferred sales category used for ABC analysis. Mandatory if the "salesCategoryValidityDate" element is filled in, otherwise should not be filled in.
+ salesCategoryValidityDate: `2025-04-14 00:00:00.000` (datetime, condition) - Validity date for preferred salability category. Mandatory if the "salesCategoryId" element is filled in, otherwise should not be filled in.
+ productPackageChange: `1` (tinyint) - Specifies whether the packaging of the product should be changed during the process of receipt. Supported values: 0 – No, 1 – Yes, the packaging must be changed during the process of receipt (unless stated otherwise on the receipt).
+ texts.text: `Be careful, fragile!` (string(32766)) - Text from ERP. Multiple texts can be sent, but only one for each type (element typeOfText).
+ texts.typeOfText: `20` (tinyint) - Type of text. Specifies in which process the text will be displayed. Supported values: 10 - Product, 20 - Receipt, 30 - Picking, 40 - Packaging, 50 - Completion, 60 - Loading, 70 - Picking and packaging, 80 - Picking and completion, 90 - Picking, packaging and completion 

<b>Extension data</b>

The collection "extensionData" can be added to the web service in order to provide additional elements that are not a part of the standard web service. See the header "Extension data" for more details. The elements labeled as "required" must be filled in only if you want to use the specific extensionData colection.

<b>Extension data - values in foreign language</b>

+ extensionData.entities.type: `Assortment` (constant, required)
+ extensionData.entities.properties.key: `Name` (constant, required)
+ extensionData.entities.properties.language: `en` (constant, required)
+ extensionData.entities.properties.value: `Original name` (string (222)) - Name of the product (EN).

<b>Extension data - manufacturer's barcode</b>

+ extensionData.entities.type: `Assortment` (constant, required)
+ extensionData.entities.properties.key: `ManufacturerBarcode` (constant, required)
+ extensionData.entities.properties.value: `150804` (string (30)) - Barcode of the manufacturer.

<b>Extension data - product colors</b>

In the WMS, product colors are recorded in a relational table with a relation to the product. In the API, colors are handled using extensionData.
+ extensionData.entities.type: `Assortment` (constant, required)
+ extensionData.entities.relations.type: `AssortmentColor` (constant, required)
+ extensionData.entities.relations.extIsId: `A34S48GE` (string (1024), required) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP.
+ extensionData.entities.relations.properties.key: `ColorType` (constant, required)
+ extensionData.entities.relations.properties.value: `20` (tinyint, required) - Supported values: 0 - Basic, 10 - Logistic, 20 - Manufacturer color
+ extensionData.entities.relations.properties.type: `ID` (constant, required) - Specifies that this is an item list field.
+ extensionData.entities.relations.properties.key: `ColorCode` (constant, required)
+ extensionData.entities.relations.properties.value: `E65BB5D2-491B-4E3F-B2F8-37E0EE0B38ED` (string (1024), required) - Unique identifier of the color - the ID is generated during the creation of the color via API - web service itemList.

<b>Extension data - product categories</b>

In the WMS, product categories are recorded in a relational table with a relation to the product. In the API, categories are handled using extensionData.
+ extensionData.entities.type: `Assortment` (constant, required)
+ extensionData.entities.relations.type: `AssortmentCategoryRel` (constant, required)
+ extensionData.entities.relations.extIsId: `B48S11LE` (string (1024), required) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP.
+ extensionData.entities.relations.properties.key: `CategoryType` (constant, condition) - Mandatory if the "value" element is filled in, otherwise should not be filled in.
+ extensionData.entities.relations.properties.value: `20` (tinyint, condition) - Mandatory if the "key" element is "CategoryType", otherwise should not be filled in. Value must be used same as is category established via API - web service itemList. Supported values: 10 - Gender, 20 - Size, 30 - Main group, 35 - Inventory group, 40 - Data replication
+ extensionData.entities.relations.properties.type: `ID` (constant, required) - Specifies that this is a item list field.
+ extensionData.entities.relations.properties.key: `CategoryCode` (constant, required)
+ extensionData.entities.relations.properties.value: `E65BB5D2-491B-4E3F-B2F8-37E0EE0B38ED` (string (1024), required) - Unique identifier of the category - the ID is generated during the creation of the category via API - web service itemList.

<b>Extension data - product seasons</b>

In the WMS, product seasons are recorded in a relational table with a relation to the product. In the API, seasons are handled using extensionData.
+ extensionData.entities.type: `Assortment` (constant, required)
+ extensionData.entities.relations.type: `AssortmentSeasonRel` (constant, required)
+ extensionData.entities.relations.extIsId: `G47J58GE` (string (1024), required) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP.
+ extensionData.entities.relations.properties.type: `ID` (constant, required) - Specifies that this is an item list field.
+ extensionData.entities.relations.properties.key: `AssortmentSeasonCode` (constant, required)
+ extensionData.entities.relations.properties.value: `3991843B-1FB7-4248-8563-AA2CA458FFE9` (string (1024), required) - Unique identifier of the season - the ID is generated during the creation of the season via API - web service itemList.

<b>Extension data - product variants</b>

In the WMS, product variants are recorded in a relational table with a relation to the product. In the API, variants are handled using extensionData.
+ extensionData.entities.type: `Assortment` (constant, required)
+ extensionData.entities.relations.type: `AssortmentVariant` (constant, required)
+ extensionData.entities.relations.extIsId: `A87J5F3E` (string (1024), required) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP.
+ extensionData.entities.relations.properties.type: `ID` (constant, required) - Specifies that this is an item list field.
+ extensionData.entities.relations.properties.key: `VariantCode` (constant, required)
+ extensionData.entities.relations.properties.value: `E65BB5D2-491B-4E3F-B2F8-37E0EE0B38ED` (string (1024), required) - Unique identifier of the variant - the ID is generated during the creation of the variant via API - web service itemList.

<b>Extension data - number of pages</b>

+ extensionData.entities.type: `Assortment` (constant, required)
+ extensionData.entities.properties.key: `NumberOfPages` (constant, required)
+ extensionData.entities.properties.value: `327` (numeric (500)) - Number of pages.

<b>Extension data - recommended price</b>

+ extensionData.entities.type: `Assortment` (constant, required)
+ extensionData.entities.properties.key: `RecommendedPrice` (constant, required)
+ extensionData.entities.properties.value: `499` (numeric (500)) - Recommended price of the product.

### Create a Product[POST /V1/product/]
When a product is created, product’s barcodes, handling equipments can be either created alongside the product (see the section "barcodes", "handling equipments" in the example) or later with separate service (see the header "Product barcode", "Product handling equipment").

