### Update a Product[PUT /V1/product/{productId}]
In the update web service, it is always necessary to send a unique identification of the changed record (ID) in the URL. The body of the update web service should contain only those elements that need to be changed (e.g. if you only need to change product's name, all the other optional elements should remain null).

Only product information may be updated using this web service, if you want to update product's barcode, use the corresponding web service.

If you need to add the collection "extensionData" which was not added during the insert, use the same elements which are used during the insert collection "extensionData".

If one of the updated values is filled in incorrectly and the validation procedure reports an error, the system will cancel the whole update - none of the changed values will be updated.

List of elements that may be updated:
+ productCode: `X415EA-EB037T` (string (150))
+ name: `Asus X415EA-EB037T Slate Grey` (string (255))
+ nameShort: `Asus X415EA` (string (150), condition) - The setting in the WMS also determines whether the value must be sent from an ERP system.
+ type: `0` (smallint)
+ subtype: `0` (tinyint)
+ measurementUnitCode: `KS` (string (1024)) - The basic unit of measurement can be updated only if there are no stock cards or documents for the given product, and the update is enabled in the WMS settings.
+ weightGross: `10.5` (numeric (15,4))
+ weightNett: `9.5` (numeric (15,4))
+ grossDimension.height: `2` (numeric (8,4))
+ grossDimension.width: `1.5` (numeric (8,4))
+ grossDimension.depth: `3.5` (numeric (8,4))
+ grossDimension.volume: `10.5` (numeric (15,4))
+ pictureUrl: `www.mystock.cz/product.png` (string (255))
+ pictureData: `/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQEASABIAAD/4gxYSUNDX1BST0ZJTEUAAQEAAAxITG` (varbinary)
+ expirationMandatory: `1` (tinyint)
+ expirationPeriod: `365` (integer, condition) - Mutually exclusive with element "expirationPeriodInMonth" - at any time only one of these two may be set. Permitted settings: 1) Both elements are undefined (null value), 2) Value of one element is set to 0 and the other element has any positive number.
+ expirationPeriodSupplier: `30` (integer)
+ expirationPeriodInMonth: `12` (integer, condition) - Mutually exclusive with element "expirationPeriod" (days) - at any time only one of these two may be set. Permitted settings: 1) Both elements are undefined (null value), 2) Value of one element is set to 0 and the other element has any positive number.
+ batches: `0` (tinyint)
+ variantMandatory: `0` (tinyint)
+ atestMandatory: `0` (tinyint)
+ serialNumbersRecords.inboundMandatory: `0` (tinyint)
+ serialNumbersRecords.outboundMandatory: `1` (tinyint)
+ manufacturerProductNumber: `BV373` (string (40))
+ storeSeparately: `0` (tinyint)
+ brandId: `BC9B92F8-71DE-449B-917C-4029E6CFA6C1` (string (1024))
+ brandId2: `90AD3F04-1489-4CC8-8FD4-3AEEE62379E7` (string (1024))
+ conversionMeasurementUnitCode: `M2` (string (1024))
+ groupId: `D959BB85-0F8F-44F5-AA2F-B028C8F69F38` (string (1024))
+ primarySupplierId: `1A3469D4-2111-4181-8CCB-969350D3433B` (string (1024))
+ description: `Description of the product` (string (32766))
+ productLabelPrint: `0` (tinyint)
+ productLabelPrintReceipt: `0` (tinyint)
+ commodityCode: `58475465` (string (14))
+ countryCode: `CZ` (string (3))
+ palletQuantity: `7` (numeric (15,4))
+ salesCategoryId: `KAT` (string (1024), condition) - Mandatory if the "salesCategoryValidityDate" element is filled in, otherwise should not be filled in.
+ salesCategoryValidityDate: `2025-04-14 00:00:00.000` (datetime, condition) - Mandatory if the "salesCategoryId" element is filled in, otherwise should not be filled in.
+ productPackageChange: `1` (tinyint)
+ texts.text: `Be careful, fragile!` (string(32766)) - If it is sent with an empty string, the text is deleted in the WMS. If multiple texts were sent via insert, the type (element typeOfText) for which we want to change or delete the text must also be specified during the update.

+ Parameters
    + productId: `A770B14D-9E31-427C-9B19-A3D79D3BE8F9` (string) - A unique identifier of the product you want to update.

+ Request (application/json)

