## Product barcode [/V1/productBarcode/]

Base URI template that is used at the end of the URL when the web service is called: <b>/V1/productBarcode/</b> (example: https://demo.mystock.cz/V1/productBarcode/).

The web service has following elements:
+ productId: `A770B14D-9E31-427C-9B19-A3D79D3BE8F9` (string (1024), required) - Unique identifier of the product - the ID is generated during the creation of the product via API.
+ barcode: `EAN3` (string (30), required) - Barcode of the product. Any string of values can be entered, usually EAN-13 is used. There is no validation of the code imported into the WMS.
+ extIsId: `648DC0FF` (string(1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP that must be used when it is not possible to ensure that the value in the element "barcode" is unique. If the identification in the element "barcode" is unique, "extIsId" should not be filled in.
+ default: `0` (tinyint) - Default barcode for the product (only one barcode can be selected as a default barcode). Supported values: 0 - No, 1 - Yes.
+ measurementUnitCode: `KS` (string (1024)) - The element is used to distinguish barcodes for different units of measurement (the unit of measurement must exist in the WMS, otherwise the record will not be imported). If there is only one (basic) unit of measurement registered in the WMS for the given product, it is not necessary to fill in the element (it can be NULL).
+ active: `1` (tinyint, required) - State of the barcode. Supported values: 0 - Inactive, 1 - Active.

### Create a Product barcode [POST /V1/productBarcode/]

Product's barcode can be created either alongside the product by using the "Create a Product" web service or after the product is already created by using the "Create a Product barcode" web service.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
        "productId": "A770B14D-9E31-427C-9B19-A3D79D3BE8F9",
        "barcode": "EAN3",
        "extIsId": "648DC0FF",
        "default": 0,
        "measurementUnitCode": "KS",
        "active": 1
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
        "data": 
            {
            "ids": [
                {
                    "id": "17D88A44-C46A-4654-BD06-9900DC0A812A",
                    "recordId": "1",
                    "sourceId": "648DC0FF",
                    "type": "productBarcode"
                }
            ]
            },
        "errors": []
        }
        
+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
            "errors": [
                {
                    "errorType": 4,
                    "errorText": "The specified unit of measurement is not registered for the given product",
                    "sourceId": "648DC0FF",
                    "recordId": "1",
                    "recordType": "productBarcode",
                    "propertyName": "measurementUnitCode"
                }
            ],
            "data": null
        }

### Update a Product barcode [PUT /V1/productBarcode/{productBarcodeId}]
In the update web service, it is always necessary to send a unique identification of the changed record (ID) in the URL. The body of the update web service must always contain all the mandatory elements (see below), other elements should be filled in only when there is need to change the information they contain (e.g. if you only need to change barcode's activity, all the other optional elements should remain null).

If one of the updated values is filled in incorrectly and the validation procedure reports an error, the system will cancel the whole update - none of the changed values will be updated.

List of elements that may be updated:
+ productId: `A770B14D-9E31-427C-9B19-A3D79D3BE8F9` (string (1024), required) - The ID of the product to which the barcode belongs. It is not possible to change the product ID within the update - if you want to assign the given barcode to another product, you must deactivate the barcode for the original product and create a new barcode for the new product.
+ default: `0` (tinyint)
+ active: `1` (tinyint)

+ Parameters
    + productBarcodeId: `17D88A44-C46A-4654-BD06-9900DC0A812A` (string) - A unique identifier of the product’s barcode you want to update.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
        "productId": "A770B14D-9E31-427C-9B19-A3D79D3BE8F9",
        "default": 0,
        "active": 1
        }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
        "data": "OK",
        "errors": []
        }
        
+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
        "data": null,
        "errors": [
            {
                "errorText": "Invalid value",
                "errorType": 3,
                "internalRecordId": null,
                "propertyName": "productId",
                "recordId": "1",
                "recordType": "productBarcode",
                "sourceId": "A770B14D-9E31-427C-9B19-A3D79D3BE8F9_KS_EAN3"
            }
            ]
        }

## Product's unit of measurement [/V1/productMeasurementUnit/]

Base URI template that is used at the end of the URL when the web service is called: <b>/V1/productMeasurementUnit/</b> (example: https://demo.mystock.cz/V1/productMeasurementUnit/).

The web service has following elements:
+ productId: `67929C3B-7C08-4B23-A8E1-79BF761C2043` (string (1024), required) - Unique identifier of the product - the ID is generated during the creation of the product via API.
+ measurementUnitCode: `BAL` (string (1024), required) - Derived unit of measurement - this unit of measurement must be registered in the unit of measurements' codebook in the WMS. Derived unit of measurement cannot be the same as the product's basic unit of measurement.
+ extIsId: `487DC0EE` (string (1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP that must be used when it is not possible to ensure that the value in the element "measurementUnitCode" is unique. If the identification in the element "measurementUnitCode" is unique, "extIsId" should not be filled in.
+ quantity: `1` (numeric (15,4), required) - Quantity of the derived unit of measurement - by default, quantity 1 should be filled in (e.g.: 1 package contains 20 pieces).
+ basicQuantity: `20` (numeric (15,4), required) - Quantity of the basic unit of measurement - the quantity stated in the basic unit of measurement, this quantity of the product is contained in the derived unit of measurement (e.g.: 20 pieces are packed in 1 package).
+ weightGross: `1,62` (numeric (18,7)) - Gross weight of the product (kg).
+ weightNett: `1,47` (numeric (18,7)) - Nett weight of the product (kg).
+ grossDimension.height: `0,12` (numeric (8,4)) - Gross height of the product (m).
+ grossDimension.width: `0,51` (numeric (8,4)) - Gross width of the product (m).
+ grossDimension.depth: `0,58` (numeric (8,4)) - Gross depth of the product (m).
+ grossDimension.volume: `0,0354` (numeric (15,4)) - Gross volume of the product (m3).
+ fullPallet: `0` (tinyint) - Pallet Unit of Measurement (Pallet UoM). Determine the UoM of the product (and therefore the quantity in the UoM record) that is equal to one EUR pallet. The quantity is determined by the producer (the producer of the product optimises the size of the packaging to fit as much of the product as possible on one pallet). The pallet UoM is used in the WMS both in receipt (automatic determination of the so-called full pallet and its height) and in shipping (if the shipped quantity is equal to the pallet UoM (or a whole multiple), it is picked in a separate shipping batch directly from the reserve location, according to the availability on the stock cards and the WMS settings). Only one UoM of the product can be defined as pallet UoM in the WMS. If the ordered quantity corresponds with the "full pallet" unit of measurement (and some full pallet is in the warehouse), the WMS will dispatch full pallet. Supported values: 0 - No, 1 - Yes
+ handlingUnit: `1` (tinyint) - Handling Unit of Measurement (Handling UoM). Determine the UoM of the product (and therefore the quantity in the UoM record) that is primary (optimal) for handling the product in the warehouse (transfers, optimization tasks - adding picking locations, etc.). It is used for rounding off WMS optimization tasks. In ERP it can be designated as stock UoM. Only one UoM of the product can be defined as handling UoM in WMS. Supported values: 0 - No, 1 - Yes 

### Create a Product‘s unit of measurement [POST /V1/productMeasurementUnit/]

Product's unit of measurement can be created either alongside the product by using the "Create a Product" web service or after the product is already created by using the "Create a Product‘s unit of measurement" web service.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
        "productId": "67929C3B-7C08-4B23-A8E1-79BF761C2043",
        "measurementUnitCode": "BAL",
        "extIsId": "487DC0EE",
