### Update a Product's unit of measurement [PUT /V1/productMeasurementUnit/{productMeasurementUnitId}]

In the update web service, it is always necessary to send a unique identification of the changed record (ID) in the URL. The body of the update web service must always contain all the mandatory elements (see below), other elements should be filled in only when there is need to change the information they contain (e.g. if you only need to change measurement unit's dimensions, all the other optional elements should remain null).

If one of the updated values is filled in incorrectly and the validation procedure reports an error, the system will cancel the whole update - none of the changed values will be updated.

List of elements that may be updated:
+ productId: `CC7008EF-8727-4BF4-AE88-C4968D87C981` (string (1024), required) - Unique identifier of the product that is generated during the creation of the product via API. The product's ID must be sent with every update of the product's unit of measurement.
+ weightGross: `2.5` (numeric (18,7))
+ weightNett: `2.4` (numeric (18,7))
+ fullPallet: `0` (tinyint)
+ handlingUnit: `0` (tinyint)
+ grossDimension.width: `66.5` (numeric (8,4))
+ grossDimension.height: `77.5` (numeric (8,4))
+ grossDimension.depth: `88.5` (numeric (8,4))
+ grossDimension.volume: `1000.5` (numeric (15,4))

+ Parameters
    + productMeasurementUnitId: `54D88A44-C46R-4744-BG76-9911DC0A212A` (string) - A unique identifier of the product's unit of measurement you want to update.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "productId": "CC7008EF-8727-4BF4-AE88-C4968D87C981",
            "weightGross": 2.5,
            "weightNett": 2.4,
            "fullPallet": 0,
            "handlingUnit": 0,
            "grossDimension": {
                "width": 66.5,
                "height": 77.5,
                "depth": 88.5,
                "volume": 1000.5
            }
        }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "errors": [],
            "data": "OK"
        }

+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
            "data": null,
            "errors": [
                {
                    "errorText": "Invalid value",
                    "errorType": 3,
                    "internalRecordId": null,
                    "propertyName": "productId",
                    "recordId": "1",
                    "recordType": "productMeasurementUnit",
                    "sourceId": "F468FA85-0F73-4864-9473-451D98689FCE"
                }
            ]
        }

## Product handling equipment [/V1/productHandlingEquipment/]

Base URI template that is used at the end of the URL when the web service is called: <b>/V1/productHandlingEquipment/</b> (example: https://demo.mystock.cz/V1/productHandlingEquipment/).

The web service has following elements:
+ extIsId: `648DC0FF` (string(1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP.
+ productId: `A770B14D-9E31-427C-9B19-A3D79D3BE8F9` (string (1024), required) - Unique identifier of the product - the ID is generated during the creation of the product via API.
+ handlingEquipmentId: `VNA` (string (1024), required) – The element is used to restrict the handling equipment to a specific quantity of units during dispatch. If handling equipment ID is specified, it must exist in the WMS, otherwise the record will not be imported.
+ minQuantity: `5` (numeric (15,4), required) – Minimum quantity for handling. This element is used to define constraints on the quantity of items to be picked by a specific type of handling equipment. The task allocation algorithm respects these limits: if the quantity of items in a task falls outside the defined range (Min–Max), the task will not be assigned to the respective equipment type.
+ maxQuantity: `25` (numeric (15,4), required) - Maximum quantity for handling. Maximum value is 999 999. This element is used to define constraints on the quantity of items to be picked by a specific type of handling equipment. The task allocation algorithm respects these limits: if the quantity of items in a task falls outside the defined range (Min–Max), the task will not be assigned to the respective equipment type.
+ active: `1` (tinyint, required) - State of the handling equipment. Supported values: 0 - Inactive, 1 - Active.

### Create a Product handling equipment [POST /V1/productHandlingEquipment/]

Product's handling equipment can be created either alongside the product by using the "Create a Product" web service or after the product is already created by using the "Create a Product handling equipment" web service.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "extIsId": "648DC0FF",
            "productId": "A770B14D-9E31-427C-9B19-A3D79D3BE8F9",
            "handlingEquipmentId": "VNA",
            "minQuantity": 5,
            "maxQuantity": 25,
            "active": 1
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
        "data": 
            {
            "ids": [
                {
                    "id": " 60279F50-6F48-465B-B15B-6C1D99FD3D77",
                    "recordId": "1",
                    "sourceId": "648DC0FF",
                    "type": "productHandlingEquipment"
                }
            ]
            },
        "errors": []
        }
        
+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
            "errors": [
                {
                    "errorType": 3,
                    "errorText": "Invalid entry",
                    "sourceId": "648DC0FF",
                    "recordId": "1",
                    "recordType": "productHandlingEquipment",
                    "propertyName": "handlingEquipmentId"
                }
            ],
            "data": null
        }

### Update a Product handling equipment [PUT /V1/productHandlingEquipment/{productHandlingEquipmentId}]
In the update web service, it is always necessary to send a unique identification of the changed record (ID) in the URL. The body of the update web service must always contain all the mandatory elements (see below), other elements should be filled in only when there is need to change the information they contain (e.g. if you only need to change handling's equipment activity, all the other optional elements should remain null).

If one of the updated values is filled in incorrectly and the validation procedure reports an error, the system will cancel the whole update - none of the changed values will be updated.

List of elements that may be updated:
+ productId: `A770B14D-9E31-427C-9B19-A3D79D3BE8F9` (string (1024), required) - The ID of the product to which the handling equipment belongs. It is not possible to change the product ID within the update - if you want to assign the given handling equipment to another product, you must deactivate the handling equipment for the original product and create a new handling equipment for the new product.
+ minQuantity: `5` (numeric (15,4), condition) - Permitted settings: 1) Both quantity elements are definied. 2) Both quantity elements are undefined (null value). Otherwise should not be filled in.
+ maxQuantity: `25` (numeric (15,4), condition) - Permitted settings: 1) Both quantity elements are definied. 2) Both quantity elements are undefined (null value). Otherwise should not be filled in.
+ active: `1` (tinyint)

+ Parameters
    + productHandlingEquipmentId: `17D88A44-C46A-4654-BD06-9900DC0A812A` (string) - A unique identifier of the product’s handling equipment you want to update.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "productId": "A770B14D-9E31-427C-9B19-A3D79D3BE8F9",
            "minQuantity": 5,
            "maxQuantity": 25,
            "active": 1
        }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
        "data": "OK",
        "errors": []
        }
        
+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
            "errors": [
                {
                    "errorType": 3,
                    "errorText": "Invalid entry",
                    "recordId": "1",
                    "recordType": "productHandlingEquipment",
                    "propertyName": "productId"
                }
            ],
            "data": null
        }

## Product group [/V1/productGroup/]
Base URI template that is used at the end of the URL when the web service is called: <b>/V1/productGroup/</b> (example: https://demo.mystock.cz/V1/productGroup/).

The web service has following elements:
+ code: `G001` (string (20), required) - Product group code from the ERP - a unique identifier that cannot be changed over time, it is used to identify product group in the WMS. The code is displayed to warehouse operators on mobile devices and is printed in reports.
+ extIsId: `4E9F5A10` (string(1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP that must be used when it is not possible to ensure that the value in the element "code" is unique. If the identification in the element "code" is unique, "extIsId" should not be filled in.
+ name: `U0001 Group` (string (40), required) - Name of the group
+ description: `Product group description` (string (255)) - Description of the group
+ parentGroupId: `D3BA69F1-173E-4179-9153-FF402F1B3EF9` (string (1024)) - ID of the parent group
+ carrierProductName: `ELECTRONICS` (string (60)) - Name of product group for delivery purposes. This information is exported via WMS into carrier's system when expeding products of this group.

### Create a Product group [POST /V1/productGroup/]
Web service for creating product groups. Product groups can have a tree structure. The web service inserts one product group at a time. A product must always be placed only in one group. If groupId is not specified in the Product web service (see Create a Product), the product is automatically assigned into the default product group.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
        "extIsId": "4E9F5A10",
        "code": "G001",
        "name": "U0001 Group",
        "description": "Product group description",
        "parentGroupId": "D3BA69F1-173E-4179-9153-FF402F1B3EF9",
        "carrierProductName": "ELECTRONICS"
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
            "data": {
                "ids": [
                    {
                        "id": "503A296D-21E2-4366-8D4F-2D76EEFD8EF8",
                        "recordId": "0",
                        "sourceId": "4E9F5A10",
                        "type": "productGroup"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "errors": []
        }

+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
            "data": null,
            "errors": [
                {
                    "errorText": "The entered value is NULL",
                    "errorType": 1,
                    "internalRecordId": null,
                    "propertyName": "code",
                    "recordId": "1",
                    "recordType": "productGroup",
                    "sourceId": "4E9F5A10"
                }
            ]
        }

### Update a Product group [PUT /V1/productGroup/{productGroupId}]
In the update web service, it is always necessary to send a unique identification of the changed record (ID) in the URL. The body of the update web service must always contain all the mandatory elements (see below), other elements should be filled in only when there is need to change the information they contain (e.g. if you only need to change group's name, all the other optional elements should remain null).

If one of the updated values is filled in incorrectly and the validation procedure reports an error, the system will cancel the whole update - none of the changed values will be updated.

List of elements that may be updated:
+ code: `G001` (string (20)) 
+ name: `U0001 Group` (string (40)) 
+ description: `Product group description` (string (255))
+ parentGroupId: `D3BA69F1-173E-4179-9153-FF402F1B3EF9` (string (1024))
+ carrierProductName: `ELECTRONICS` (string (60))

+ Parameters
    + productGroupId: `CBDD9EB9-D28D-4871-94AE-BE26DBC536DD` (string) - A unique identifier of the product’s group you want to update.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "code": "G001",
            "name": "U0001 Group",
            "description": "Product group description",
            "parentGroupId": "D3BA69F1-173E-4179-9153-FF402F1B3EF9",
            "carrierProductName": "ELECTRONICS"
        }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
        "data": "OK",
        "errors": []
        }
        
+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
            "errors": [
                {
                    "errorType": 3,
                    "errorText": "Invalid entry",
                    "sourceId": "<<NULL>>",
                    "recordId": "1",
                    "recordType": "productGroup",
                    "propertyName": "parentGroupId"
                }
            ],
            "data": null
        }
 
## Item list [/V1/itemList/]

Base URI template that is used at the end of the URL when the web service is called: <b>/V1/itemList/</b> (example: https://demo.mystock.cz/V1/itemList/).

The web service has following elements:
+ code: `Blue-color` (string (20), condition) - Item list code from the ERP - a unique identifier that cannot be changed over time, it is used to identify item list in the WMS.
+ extIsId: `648DC0FF` (string (1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP that must be used when it is not possible to ensure that the value in the element "code" is unique. If the identification in the element "code" is unique, "extIsId" should not be filled in.
+ type: `Color` (string (150), required) - Supported types: Color, AssortmentBrand, AssortmentSeason, AssortmentCategory, LotVariant
+ name: `Blue` (string (32766), required) - Name of the item list.
+ extensionData: (string (32766)) - External data, see the header "Extension data".

### Create an Item list - Product color [POST /V1/itemList/]
Item list of colors.

The web service has following elements:
The basic elements are the same as for the Item list service, only the extensionData content is different.
+ extensionData.entities.type: `Color` (constant, required)
+ extensionData.entities.properties.key: `Description` (constant, required)
+ extensionData.entities.properties.value: `Description of the blue color` (string (255)) - Description of the color.


