## Document [/V1/document/]
Base URI template that is used at the end of the URL when the web service is called: <b>/V1/document/</b> (example: https://demo.mystock.cz/V1/document/).

The web service has following elements:
+ primaryRecordType: `orderIncomingItem` (string(1024), condition) – Used to identify the primary record to which the attachment belongs to (e.g.: "orderIncoming", "orderIncomingItem", "Receipt", "ShippingUnit", …). Mandatory if the "saveAsAttachment" element is "1", otherwise should not be filled in.
+ primaryRecordTypeKind: ` ` (string(1024), condition) - Used to identify the primary record to which the attachment belongs to. If the document is imported to a record that is transferred within a web service (except the "extensionData" collection or the "Item list" web service), the "primaryRecordTypeKind" element should not be filled. Supported values:
<br>ItemList – Use this value for records stored by the ItemList service, the value from the "type" item of this service is filled in the element "primaryRecordType".</br>
<br>ExtensionData – Use this value for records stored by extensionsData, the "type" value of the object from the relations collection is filled in the element "primaryRecordType".</br>
<br>Wms – Use this value for records stored only in the WMS. At the same time, element "primaryRecordType"must be filled in (e.g. for logistic units, "primaryRecordType" is "ShippingUnit").</br>

+ primaryRecordId: `10804573-b67e717c-2489-4809-9ccd-f49e0ce4b7ec` (string(1024), condition) - Used to identify the primary record to which the attachment belongs to. The ID of the record is specified.
+ print: `1` (tinyint) – Defines whether the files should be printed. Supported values: 
<br>0 - Do not print</br>
<br>1 - Print</br>
+ printerName: `epson` (string(60), condition) - The name of the printer in the operating system to which physical printing should be directed. Mandatory if the value of the print element is „1“.
+ printCopiesCount: `1` (integer, condition) – Number of copies. Mandatory if the value of the print element is „1“. 
+ saveAsAttachment: `1` (tinyint, condition) – Defines whether the file should be saved as an attachment. Supported values:
<br>0 - Do not save as attachment (Insert does not return an identification.)</br>
<br>1 - Save as attachment</br>
+ files.extIsId: `file001` (string(1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP.
+ files.fileName: `invoice_1.pdf` (string(255), required) - The name of the file to print or to save attachment. If the saveAsAttachment element is „1", then the file name is checked and must not contain characters: \ / : * ? " < > |
+ files.printoutControlCode: `CONTROL_CODE` (string(60), condition) - It serves for the control identification of the printed file, for example when inserting it into packaging. Can be filled in if the saveAsAttachment element is „1“, otherwise should not be filled in.
+ files.attachmentGroupId: `orderIncomingItem-invoices` (string(1024), condition) - Specifies the attachment group that defines the target attachment storage. Can be filled in if the saveAsAttachment element is „1“, otherwise should not be filled in. It must be filled in if there are multiple groups in WMS for the given type.
+ files.attachmentTypeId: `invoice` (string(1024)) – Attachments can be differentiated by using preconfigured types. For example, to record attachments to an order incoming, types can be configured for attachments such as delivery note reports, invoices, packing list etc.
+ files.data: `VGVzdG92YWNpU291Ym9yDQpPYnNhaA0KS29uZWMgc291Ym9ydQ==` (varbinary, required) – The content of the file that is stored in Base64 binary form.

### Create a Document [POST /V1/document/]
It is possible to save multiple files to one primary record (e.g. an order incoming) calling the „Document“ web service. The document content is encoded as a Base64String. The size of all files in one message is limited (default to 20 MB - can be set by the WMS). 

Insert returns an identification for each file that was created.

If an error occurs during the creation of the document, no value is inserted into the WMS database.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "primaryRecordType": "orderIncomingItem",
            "primaryRecordTypeKind": null,
            "primaryRecordId": "10804573-b67e717c-2489-4809-9ccd-f49e0ce4b7ec",
            "print": 1,
            "printerName": "epson",
            "printCopiesCount": 1,
            "saveAsAttachment": 1,
            "files": [
                {
                    "extIsId": "file001",
                    "fileName": "invoice_1.pdf",
                    "printoutControlCode": "CONTROL_CODE",
                    "attachmentGroupId": "orderIncomingItem-invoices",
                    "attachmentTypeId": "invoice",
                    "data": "VGVzdG92YWNpU291Ym9yDQpPYnNhaA0KS29uZWMgc291Ym9ydQ=="
                },
                {
                    "extIsId": "file002",
                    "fileName": "delivery_note.pdf",
                    "attachmentGroupId": "orderIncomingItem-deliveryNotes",
                    "attachmentTypeId": "deliveryNote",
                    "data": "JKAzdG22YWNpU254Ym9yDQpPYmMhaA0KR45uZWMgc223Ym9yqD=="
                }
            ]
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
            "errors": [],
            "data": {
                "ids": [
                    {
                        "id": "F12C275A-6A36-4D11-AFCC-C94442F0FB98",
                        "recordId": "1",
                        "sourceId": "file001",
                        "type": "Document"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "E2CD64EB-FAD5-4B11-81C1-BF973168E645",
                        "recordId": "2",
                        "sourceId": "file002",
                        "type": "Document"
                    }
                ]
            }
        }
               
+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
            "errors": [
                {
                    "errorType": 3,
                    "errorText": "Invalid entry",
                    "sourceId": "file002",
                    "recordId": "1",
                    "recordType": "Document",
                    "propertyName": "files.attachmentTypeId"
                }
            ],
            "data": null
        }

### Update a Document [PUT /V1/document/{documentId}]
In the update web service, it is always necessary to send a unique identification of the changed record (ID) in the URL. The body of the update web service should contain only those elements that need to be changed.

If one of the updated values is filled in incorrectly and the validation procedure reports an error, the system will cancel the whole update - none of the changed values will be updated.

Only one specific document can be updated at a time (according to the given ID of the document).

List of elements that may be updated:
+ fileName: `invoice_1_update.pdf` (string(255))
+ data: `VGVzdG92YWNpU291Ym9yDQpPYnNhaA0KS29uZWMgc291Ym9ydQ==` (varbinary, condition) - Mandatory if the value of the print element is „1“. 
+ attachmentTypeId: `invoice` (string(1024)) 
+ print: `1` (tinyint)
+ printerName: `epson` (string(60), condition) - Mandatory if the value of the print element is „1“, otherwise should not be filled in.
+ printCopiesCount: `1` (integer, condition) - Mandatory if the value of the print element is „1“, otherwise should not be filled in.

+ Parameters
    + documentId: `4D63AD01-B5F8-4B1F-9F4B-863C135926C0` (string) - A unique identifier of the document you want to update.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "fileName": "invoice_1_update.pdf",
            "data": "VGVzdG92YWNpU291Ym9yDQpPYnNhaA0KS29uZWMgc291Ym9ydQ==",
            "attachmentTypeId": "invoice",
            "print": 1,
            "printerName": "epson",
            "printCopiesCount": 1
        }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
        "data": "OK",
        "errors": []
        }
        
+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
            "errors": [
                {
                    "errorType": 2,
                    "errorText": "The entered value is different than the allowed values (0,1)",
                    "sourceId": "file001",
                    "recordId": "1",
                    "recordType": "Document",
                    "propertyName": "print",
                    "internalRecordId": "02AE8053-371E-4E66-BC65-C3137AD2E41B"
                }
            ],
            "data": null
        }

### Delete a Document [DELETE /V1/document/{documentId}]

In order to cancel a document, it is necessary to send the unique identification (ID) of the document that is to be cancelled. The result is the cancellation of the entire document.

+ Parameters
    + documentId: `5DC73A08-AC06-4B24-BFAF-32DE2E42A102` (string, required) - A unique identifier of the document you want to cancel.

+ Request (application/json)

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
        "data": "OK",
        "errors": []
        }
        
+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
        "data": null,
        "errors": [
            {
                "errorText": "Invalid entry",
                "errorType": 3,
                "internalRecordId": null,
                "propertyName": "id",
                "recordId": "0",
                "recordType": "document",
                "sourceId": null
            }
            ]
        }

## Extension data [/V1/example]
Extension data is used to transfer separate fields or records in relational tables that are not registered as standard web service elements in the mySTOCK API.

Levels of the extension data:

<b>Entities</b> are used for distinguishing the table in the WMS into which the data is to be inserted. The value in the "type" element is filled in with a constant (this constant represents the defined table name in the WMS).

<b>Properties</b> are used to define the data that are to be filled into the selected table (these are the elements that are not a part of the standard API web services). The "key" element specifies a specific field in the WMS (the field value is a constant), to which the value specified in the "value" element is to be added. In the "properties" level, it is also possible to define foreign language names for selected fields, the "language" element with the value of a specific language (e.g. "en" for English) is used for this purpose. If the elements are listed in a certain order, this order must be respected.

<b>Relations</b> are used to add data to the relational tables that are linked to the table defined in the "entities" level. The value in the "type" element is filled with a constant (this constant represents the defined name of the table in the WMS), the "extIsId" element contains the unique identification of the record in the ERP system (to the given "extIsId" the API subsequently generates and sends a standard ID, which is used in all other communications related to this record), the "properties" level defines the individual columns and their values to be added to the relational table in the WMS (the "type" element with the "ID" value specifies that it is a numeric field).

### Insert Extension data 
Extension data are currently used in the following web services: Product, Item list and Order incoming.

### Update Extension data [PUT /V1/example/{exampleId}]
To update records that were created by using the extension data collection, the same web service that created the records is always used. At the "relations" level, you need to replace the element "extIsId" with the element "id" and include the ID that was returned by the web service during the insert. Only the elements that are to be changed should be listed in the "properties" level.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
          "extensionData": {
            "entities": [
              {
                "type": "Assortment",
                "relations": [
                  {
                    "type": "AssortmentColor",
                    "id": "97B12B7D-15CB-4101-944F-6DC27F7B7155",
                    "properties": [
                      {
                        "type": "ID",
                        "key": "ColorCode",
                        "value": "40E80311-D2BA-4AAB-8281-9F71229635A5"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
            "errors": [],
            "data": "OK"
        }

### Delete Extension data [DELETE /V1/example/{exampleId}]
To delete records that were created using the extension data collection, the same web service that created the records is always used. At the "relations" level, you need to replace the element "extIsId" with the element "id" and include the ID that was returned by the web service during the insert. To delete a record, the element "valid" with the value 0 must be specified in the "properties" level. No other elements may be specified.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
          "extensionData": {
            "entities": [
              {
                "type": "Assortment",
                "relations": [
                  {
                    "type": "AssortmentColor",
                    "id": "97B12B7D-15CB-4101-944F-6DC27F7B7155",
                    "properties": [
                      {
                        "key": "Valid",
                        "value": "0"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
            "errors": [],
            "data": "OK"
        }

## Despatch advice [/V1/despatchAdvice/]
Base URI template that is used at the end of the URL when the web service is called: <b>/V1/despatchAdvice/</b> (example: https://demo.mystock.cz/V1/despatchAdvice/).

The web service has following elements:
+ despatchAdviceCode: `AV000001` (string (20), condition) - Despatch advice code from the ERP system. Each despatch advice code should be unique - if this cannot be ensured, it is necessary to use the element "extIsId".
+ extIsId: `despatchAdvice-001` (string (1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP that must be used when it is not possible to ensure that the value in the element "despatchAdviceCode" is unique. If the identification in the element "despatchAdviceCode" is unique, "extIsId" should not be filled in.
+ wmsWarehouseCode: `1` (string (20)) - Warehouse code from the WMS.
+ partnerId: `7043ECD4-5CDC-42D6-8DB2-866141C67010` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the partner - the ID is generated during the creation of the partner via API.
+ operatingUnitId: `1AF1F2F0-01E4-4331-A166-491A176B2878` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the partner's operating unit - the ID is generated during the creation of the partner's operating unit via API.
+ deliveryDateTimeFrom: `2022-10-21 00:00:00.000` (datetime) - The earliest date and time of expected arrival.
+ deliveryDateTimeTo: `2022-10-21 23:59:59.000` (datetime) - The latest date and time of expected arrival.
+ licensePlateNumber: `3T4 3432` (string (20)) - Vehicle license plate number.
+ despatchNote: `note` (string (255)) - Supplier's note.
+ receipts.extIsId: `despatchAdvice-001-receipt-01` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the record in relation to a receipt.
+ receipts.receiptId: `2133D60B-DDD6-4786-BF06-D58770161A6A` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the receipt - the ID is generated during the creation of the receipt via API.

<b>Logistic Units</b>

Optional collection of the logistics units which contains packaging information. A logistics unit can contain products or a collection of logistics units (i.e. a pallet contains cartons and these contain products).  
If it is not an adviced receipt, this information is not sent. Only the despatch advice is sent.
+ logisticUnits.extIsId: `despatchAdvice-001-logUnit-01` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the logistics unit record.
+ logisticUnits.logisticUnitCode: `LU001` (string (35)) - The logistics unit code which must be unique within the advice. The element is mandatory if the API is configured to check for duplicate inserts using code column.
+ logisticUnits.serialShippingContainerCode: `120000000000000142` (string (50)) - Transport label (for example SSCC).
+ logisticUnits.packageTypeDescription: `Description` (string (100)) - Description of the type of packaging.
+ logisticUnits.partnerId: `63D7132B-3534-45B6-AD4F-5013FD505F35` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the partner - the ID is generated during the creation of the partner via API.
+ logisticUnits.operatingUnitId: `26546DF0-BB13-4243-984E-3FA56DBCF650` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the partner's operating unit - the ID is generated during the creation of the partner's operating unit via API.
+ logisticUnits.grossDimension.height: `10.1` (numeric (8,1)) - Height of the logistic unit (mm)
+ logisticUnits.grossDimension.width: `20.2` (numeric (8,1)) - Width of the logistic unit (mm)
+ logisticUnits.grossDimension.depth: `30.3` (numeric (8,1)) - Depth of the logistic unit (mm)
+ logisticUnits.weightGross: `4.4` (numeric (18,7)) - Weight of the logistic unit (kg)

<b>Receipts</b>

A collection of receipts related to a logistics unit. Can only be specified for a logistics unit containing items.
+ logisticUnits.receipts.extIsId: `despatchAdvice-001-logUnit-01-receipt-01` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the record in relation to a receipt.
+ logisticUnits.receipts.receiptId: `9AC9B2B3-4A8B-4BBC-8DCF-4EBCF469BFDC` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the receipt - the ID is generated during the creation of the receipt via API.

<b>Items</b>

Collection of items 
+ logisticUnits.items.extIsId: `despatchAdvice-009-logUnit-01-item-01` (string (1024)) -Unique identifier of the item record.
+ logisticUnits.items.itemCode: `item 01` (string (40)) - Receipt item code in the external system.
+ logisticUnits.items.productId: `F4ABE098-DE4D-4F84-B26D-7BBE8F4F6627` (string (1024), required) - Unique identifier of the product.
+ logisticUnits.items.amount.measurementUnitCode: `KS` (string (5)) - Unit of measurement in which the product is issued from the warehouse - the code is generated during the creation of the unit of measurement in the WMS. If there is no value filled in, system uses the basic unit of measurement for the ordered product.
+ logisticUnits.items.amount.quantity: `1` (numeric (17,6), required) - Quantity of the product (in basic unit of measurement, if there is no other unit of measurement filled in).

### Create a Despatch advice [POST /V1/despatchAdvice/]

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "extIsId": "despatchAdvice-001",
            "despatchAdviceCode": "AV000001",
            "wmsWarehouseCode": "1",
            "partnerId": "7043ECD4-5CDC-42D6-8DB2-866141C67010",
            "operatingUnitId": "1AF1F2F0-01E4-4331-A166-491A176B2878",
            "deliveryDateTimeFrom": "2022-10-21 00:00:00.000",
            "deliveryDateTimeTo": "2022-10-21 23:59:59.000",
            "licensePlateNumber": "3T4 3432",
            "despatchNote": "note",
            "receipts": [
                {
                    "extIsId": "despatchAdvice-001-receipt-01",
                    "receiptId": "2133D60B-DDD6-4786-BF06-D58770161A6A"
                }
            ],
            "logisticUnits": [
                {
                    "extIsId": "despatchAdvice-001-logUnit-01",
                    "logisticUnitCode": "LU001",
                    "serialShippingContainerCode": "120000000000000142",
                    "packageTypeDescription": "Description",
                    "partnerId": "63D7132B-3534-45B6-AD4F-5013FD505F35",
                    "operatingUnitId": "26546DF0-BB13-4243-984E-3FA56DBCF650",
                    "grossDimension": {
                        "height": 10.1,
                        "width": 20.2,
                        "depth": 30.3
                    },
                    "weightGross": 4.4,
                    "receipts": [
                        {
                            "extIsId": "despatchAdvice-001-logUnit-01-receipt-01",
                            "receiptId": "9AC9B2B3-4A8B-4BBC-8DCF-4EBCF469BFDC"
                        }
                    ],
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "extIsId": "despatchAdvice-001-logUnit-01-item-01",
                            "itemCode": "item 01",
                            "productId": "F4ABE098-DE4D-4F84-B26D-7BBE8F4F6627",
                            "amount": {
                                "measurementUnitCode": "KS",
                                "quantity": 1
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
        
+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
            "errors": [],
            "data": {
                "ids": [
                    {
                        "id": "1039cba7-dbd4-441a-b7e9-524fdab8a37f",
                        "recordId": "1",
                        "sourceId": "despatchAdvice-001",
                        "type": "despatchAdvice"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "8308111a-aec5-4c2d-a12f-b8717b6f2fde",
                        "recordId": "1",
                        "sourceId": "despatchAdvice-001-logUnit-01",
                        "type": "despatchAdviceLogisticUnit"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "4ab1338d-dd85-4826-bebf-9d3112e4c4e5",
                        "recordId": "1",
                        "sourceId": "despatchAdvice-001-logUnit-01-item-01",
                        "type": "despatchAdviceLogisticUnitItem"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "4a1df26a-25e8-4d5d-b375-dd1dcc1c8a2f",
                        "recordId": "1",
                        "sourceId": "despatchAdvice-001-receipt-01",
                        "type": "despatchAdviceReceiptRelation"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "5fb79c2b-f375-4e44-b3a9-84eddf6ba4a9",
                        "recordId": "2",
                        "sourceId": "despatchAdvice-001-logUnit-01-receipt-01",
                        "type": "despatchAdviceReceiptRelation"
                    }
                ]
            }
        }

+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
            "errors": [
                {
                    "errorType": 5,
                    "errorText": "The logical key is not unique",
                    "sourceId": "despatchAdvice-001",
                    "recordId": "1",
                    "recordType": "despatchAdvice",
                    "propertyName": "extIsId",
                    "internalRecordId": "1039cba7-dbd4-441a-b7e9-524fdab8a37f"
                }
            ],
            "data": null
        }
        
## Receipt [/V1/receipt/]

Base URI template that is used at the end of the URL when the web service is called: <b>/V1/receipt/</b> (example: https://demo.mystock.cz/V1/receipt/).

<b>Each item in the receipt must be unique – there must not be two items with identical products and attributes in one document.</b>

The web service has following elements:
+ receiptCode: `R-13305` (string (20), required) - Receipt code from the ERP system. Each receipt code should be unique - if this cannot be ensured, it is necessary to use the element "extIsId".
+ extIsId: `B6E7146E` (string(1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP that must be used when it is not possible to ensure that the value in the element "receiptCode" is unique. If the identification in the element "receiptCode" is unique, "extIsId" should not be filled in.
+ type: `1` (tinyint, required) - Supported receipt types: Internal (`0`) - Internal receipt (e.g. surplus from inventory check, newly assembled products, reprocessed products, ...), External (`1`) - External receipt from the supplier, From the customer (`10`) - Receipt from the customer. It is also possible to send a user-defined value. The allowable range is 90000 - 99999. A user-defined value can be combined with an element "specification".
+ warehouseCode: `1` (string (20), condition) - Warehouse code from the ERP. If the attribute "external warehouse" is switched on in the WMS, the warehouse code might be filled in for every item - in that case the warehouse code from the header is valid for all receipt items without a separately filled warehouse code. If the warehouse code is filled on both the item and the header, the value from the item takes precedence.
+ centerCode: `CEN01` (string (20), condition) - Center code must be filled in only for the internal receipts (type: `0`), the element should not be filled in for the other receipt types.
+ partnerId: `4D63AD01-B5F8-4B1F-9F4B-863C135926C0` (string (1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the partner - the ID is generated during the creation of the partner via API. Partner's ID must be filled in for the external receipts (type: `1`) and the receipts from the customer (type: `10`).
+ operatingUnitId: `1A672B37-B674-4F14-A13F-C82EAF53BF15` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the partner's operating unit  - the ID is generated during the creation of the partner's operating unit via API. Fill in only if the partnerId is filled in as well.
+ priority: `100` (numeric (3)) - Receipt's priority, higher number means higher priority of the inserted receipt. The priority can range from `-999` to `999`.
+ receiptDate: `2021-01-24 00:00:00.000` (datetime, required) - Scheduled date of receipt at the warehouse.
+ differentQuantitySolution: `10` (tinyint) - Method of resolving the differences between the quantity received and the quantity expected. Supported values: `0` - Accept differences without notification, `10` - Notify and allow to accept both higher quantity and an extra item, `15` - Notify and allow to accept higher quantity, but not an extra item, `20` - Notify and do not allow to accept higher quantity nor an extra item, `30` - Notify and do not allow to accept different quantity nor an extra item.
+ note: `First receipt` (string (255)) - Note regarding the receipt.
+ despatchAdviceId: `1039cba7-dbd4-441a-b7e9-524fdab8a37f` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the despatch advice to which the receipt is linked.
+ specification: `SPEC_01` (string (20)) - Specification of the receipt.
+ texts.text: `Be careful, fragile products in the box!` (string(32766)) - Text from ERP.
+ texts.typeOfText: `20` (tinyint) - Type of text. Specifies in which process the text will be displayed. Supported values: 20 - Receipt

+ items.itemCode: `R-13305/001` (string(40)) - Unique identifier of the receipt's item (might be arranged for example as "receipt code/item code"). Each item code should be unique - if this cannot be ensured, it is necessary to use the element "items.extIsId".
+ items.extIsId: `648DC0FF` (string(1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP that must be used when it is not possible to ensure that the value in the element "items.itemCode" is unique. If the identification in the element "items.itemCode" is unique, "items.extIsId" should not be filled in.
+ items.productId: `A770B14D-9E31-427C-9B19-A3D79D3BE8F9` (string (1024), required) - Unique identifier of the product. For internal receipts you can use same values for multiple items.
+ items.amount.quantity:  `7` (numeric (15,4)) - Quantity of the product (in basic unit of measurement, if there is no other unit of measurement filled in).
+ items.amount.measurementUnitCode: `KS` (string (1024)) - Unit of measurement in which the product is issued from the warehouse - the code is generated during the creation of the unit of measurement in the WMS. If there is no value filled in, system uses the basic unit of measurement for the ordered product.
+ items.locationCode: `LOC012053` (string (20), condition) - Location code from the WMS used for product receipt. The element is required and filled in only for the internal receipts where it is used for example as a default location for the newly assembled products.
+ items.warehouseCode: `1` (string (20), condition) - Warehouse code from the ERP valid for the particular item. Fill in only if the attribute "external warehouse" is switched on in the WMS. If the warehouse code is not filled in, WMS works with the warehouse code from the header.
+ items.qualityControlStatus: `30` (tinyint, required) - If a quality control is to be performed, the ERP sends the value 5 or 10. If a quality control is not to be carried out, the ERP sends the value 20 or 30. Supported values: `0` - Not specified, `5` - For inspection during receipt, `10` - For inspection, `20` - Cleared, `30` - Blocked.
+ items.name: `Dell G5 15 Gaming (5521) Special Edition` (string(222)) - Name of the receipt's item. If it is not specified, the WMS will automatically use the name of the product.
+ items.commission: `C208211` (string(20)) - The commission code for which the product is received. Fill in only if the attribute "commission" is switched on in the WMS.
+ items.batch: `LOT220217` (string(100)) - The production batch code under which the product is received. Fill in only if the attribute "batch" is switched on in the WMS. For internal receipts you can use same values for multiple items.
+ items.batchExt: `LOT_2254` (string(20)) - Batch code recorded in the ERP.
+ items.expirationDate: `2023-09-24` (datetime) - Expiration date of the production batch. Fill in only if the attribute "batch" is switched on in the WMS. For internal receipts you can use same values for multiple items.
+ items.note: `First item` (string (255)) - Note regarding the receipt's item.
+ items.correctedDocumentId: `71D54E56-F32A-4DCC-961A-D399B2B0DB19` (string (1024)) - Primary receipt header (used for correction documents). Unique identifier of the document.
+ items.correctedItemId: `B587A515-1BF0-46A9-8166-9319FD962C2D` (string (1024)) - Primary item (used for correction documents). Unique identifier of the document item.
+ items.atestMandatory: `10` (tinyint) - Is used to specify the receipt item, whether or not an atest is required on the receipt, regardless of the product setting. Supported values: 10 - Yes, 20 - No, 30 - According to the product settings (default value).
+ items.qualityId: `DCE838E1-5A27-48EF-9746-7E1C62791776` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the quality. A property of the stock card that defines the level of its quality. (filled in only if the quality is being recorded and the attribute "quality" is switched on in the WMS)
+ items.quantityToInspect:  `5` (numeric (15,4)) - The quantity of the total quantity of the item to be inspected in the WMS processes.
+ items.productLabelPrint: `0` (tinyint) - Defines whether the product should be labeled during the receipt. Supported values: 0 - No, 1 - Yes.
+ items.productPackageChange: `10` (tinyint) - Specifies whether the packaging of the product should be changed during the process of receipt. This is a setting for a given item, which takes precedence over the settings for the product (see the element productPackageChange in the Receipt web service). Supported values: 10 – Yes, the packaging must be changed during the process of receipt, 20 – No.
+ items.texts.text: `Be careful, fragile!` (string(32766)) - Text from ERP.
+ items.texts.typeOfText: `20` (tinyint) - Type of text. Specifies in which process the text will be displayed. Supported values: 20 - Receipt

### Create a Receipt [POST /V1/receipt/]

During the creation of a receipt, the receipt header is created along with all receipt items. If an error occurs during the creation of the receipt, no value (neither header nor receipt items) is inserted into the WMS database.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "receiptCode": "R-13305",
            "extIsId": "B6E7146E",
            "type": 1,
            "warehouseCode": "1",
            "centerCode": "C001",
            "partnerId": "4D63AD01-B5F8-4B1F-9F4B-863C135926C0",
            "operatingUnitId": "1A672B37-B674-4F14-A13F-C82EAF53BF15",
            "priority": 100,
            "receiptDate": "2021-07-26 00:00:00.000",
            "differentQuantitySolution": 10,
            "note": "First receipt",
            "despatchAdviceId": "1039cba7-dbd4-441a-b7e9-524fdab8a37f",
            "specification": "SPEC_01",
            "texts": [
                {
                    "text": "Be careful, fragile products in the box!",
                    "typeOfText": 20
                }
            ],
            "items": [
                {
                    "amount": {
                        "measurementUnitCode": "KS",
                        "quantity": 5
                    },
                    "productId": "A770B14D-9E31-427C-9B19-A3D79D3BE8F9",
                    "locationCode": "LOC012053",
                    "warehouseCode": null,
                    "qualityControlStatus": 30,
                    "note": "First item",
                    "itemCode": "R-13305/001",
                    "extIsId": "648DC0FF",
                    "name": "Dell G5 15 Gaming (5521) Special Edition",
                    "commission": "C208211",
                    "batch": "LOT220217",
                    "batchExt": "LOT_2254",
                    "expirationDate": "2023-09-24",
                    "correctedDocumentId": "71D54E56-F32A-4DCC-961A-D399B2B0DB19",
                    "correctedItemId": "B587A515-1BF0-46A9-8166-9319FD962C2D",
                    "atestMandatory": 10,
                    "qualityId": "DCE838E1-5A27-48EF-9746-7E1C62791776",
                    "quantityToInspect": 5,
