### Update a Receipt [PUT /V1/receipt/{receiptId}]

In the update web service, it is always necessary to send a unique identification of the changed record (ID) in the URL. The body of the update web service should contain only those elements that need to be changed (e.g. if you only need to change receipt's date, all the other optional elements should remain null).

If it is requested to update an item, the item’s identification (element "itemId") must be filled in.

In order to add a new item to the receipt, it is necessary to send the item without the element "itemId" filled in (when the "itemId" is filled in, the web service tries to update that item). When adding a new item, all the required information for that item (see the part "Create a Receipt") must be filled in.

If one of the updated values is filled in incorrectly and the validation procedure reports an error, the system will cancel the whole update - none of the changed values will be updated.

It is not possible to update internal receipt (receipt type 0 and 9xxxx).

<b>Update of the header</b>

Update is possible until the moment the receipt processing starts in the WMS.
This applies for the elements:
+ receiptDate: `2024-07-26 00:00:00.000` (datetime)
+ differentQuantitySolution: `10` (tinyint)

Update is possible until the moment the receipt processing is completed in the WMS.
This applies for the elements:
+ priority: `100` (numeric (3))
+ note: `First receipt` (string (255))
+ texts.text: `Be careful, fragile products in the box!` (string(32766)) - If it is sent with an empty string, the text is deleted in the WMS.

<b>Update of the item</b>

Update is possible until the initiation of the item receipt in the WMS.
This applies for the elements:
+ items.amount.measurementUnitCode: `KS` (string (1024))
+ items.locationCode: `LOC012053` (string (20))
+ items.qualityControlStatus: `30` (tinyint)
+ items.name: `Dell G5 15 Gaming (5521) Special Edition` (string (222))
+ items.note: `First item` (string (255))
+ items.batchExt: `LOT_2254` (string(20))
+ items.productLabelPrint: `0` (tinyint)
+ items.texts.text: `Be careful, fragile!` (string(32766)) - If it is sent with an empty string, the text is deleted in the WMS.

<b>Update of the item’s quantity</b>

Increasing the quantity – the element „quantity“ can be updated until the processing of the receipt is completed in the WMS.

Decreasing the quantity – the element „quantity“ can only be updated until the processing of the receipt is started in the WMS.

This applies for the element:
+ items.amount.quantity:  `7` (numeric (15,4))

<b>Deleting an item</b>

Deleting an item is not allowed – however, it is possible to reset the quantity of the item. It is necessary to change the quantity in the item to the value of 0 (before starting the processing of the item).

<b>Adding an item</b>

A new item can be added only until the processing of the receipt is completed in the WMS, and the receipt must not be in an irreparable/non-editable state.

Adding a new item to an existing receipt is allowed through the receipt update web service:
1) If an item with the ID of an existing item (itemId) is sent, an update of that item is performed.
2) If an item is sent without a filled ID (itemId), a check is made to ensure that all mandatory values are filled in. If they are, a new item is created.

Element:
+ items.itemId: `47EB0C4C-BC5D-4ADF-85C6-FE9D1A6D3B7A` (string (1024)) – Not eligible for update, itemId is used only for identification of the item that is to be updated.

+ Parameters
    + receiptId: `3327C671-8AB7-4DF2-8802-1E5683ECFDE5` (string) - A unique identifier of the receipt you want to update.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "receiptDate": "2024-07-26 00:00:00.000",
            "differentQuantitySolution": 10,
            "priority": 100,
            "note": "First receipt",
            "texts": [
                {
                    "text": "Be careful, fragile products in the box!"
                }
            ],
            "items": [
                {
                    "itemId": "47EB0C4C-BC5D-4ADF-85C6-FE9D1A6D3B7A",
                    "amount": {
                        "measurementUnitCode": "KS",
                        "quantity": 7
                    },
                    "locationCode": "LOC012053",
                    "qualityControlStatus": 30,
                    "name": "Dell G5 15 Gaming (5521) Special Edition",
                    "note": "First item",
                    "productLabelPrint": 0,
                    "texts": [
                        {
                            "text": "Be careful, fragile!"
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "amount": {
                        "measurementUnitCode": "KS",
                        "quantity": 5
                    },
                    "productId": "A770B14D-9E31-427C-9B19-A3D79D3BE8F9",
                    "locationCode": "LOC012053",
                    "warehouseCode": null,
                    "qualityControlStatus": 30,
                    "note": "First item",
                    "itemCode": "R-13305/001",
                    "extIsId": "648DC0FF",
                    "name": "Dell G5 15 Gaming (5521) Special Edition",
                    "commission": "C208211",
                    "batch": "LOT220217",
                    "batchExt": "LOT_2254",
                    "expirationDate": "2023-09-24",
                    "correctedDocumentId": "71D54E56-F32A-4DCC-961A-D399B2B0DB19",
                    "correctedItemId": "B587A515-1BF0-46A9-8166-9319FD962C2D",
                    "atestMandatory": 10
                }
            ]
        }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "errors": [],
            "data": {
                "ids": [
                    {
                        "id": "C5A0C93D-9913-422D-937F-835CEFE80112",
                        "recordId": "2",
                        "sourceId": "648DC0FF",
                        "type": "receiptItem"
                    }
                ]
            }
        }
        
+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
        "data": null,
        "errors": [
            {
                "errorText": "Invalid value",
                "errorType": 3,
                "internalRecordId": null,
                "propertyName": "priority",
                "recordId": "0",
                "recordType": "receipt",
                "sourceId": "B6E7146E"
            }
            ]
        }

## Order incoming [/V1/orderIncoming/]

Base URI template that is used at the end of the URL when the web service is called: <b>/V1/orderIncoming/</b> (example: https://demo.mystock.cz/V1/orderIncoming/).

The web service has following elements:
+ orderCode: `DL-13305` (string (20), required) - Order code from the ERP system. Each order code should be unique - if this cannot be ensured, it is necessary to use the element "extIsId".
+ extIsId: `E17C51BF` (string(1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP that must be used when it is not possible to ensure that the value in the element "orderCode" is unique. If the identification in the element "orderCode" is unique, "extIsId" should not be filled in.
+ type: `1` (tinyint, required) - Supported order types: External (1), To supplier (10).
+ warehouseCode: `1` (string (20), condition) - Warehouse code from the ERP. If the attribute "external warehouse" is switched on in the WMS, the warehouse code might be filled in for every item - in that case the warehouse code from the header is valid for all order incoming items without a separately filled warehouse code. If the warehouse code is filled on both the item and the header, the value from the item takes precedence.
+ partnerId: `4D63AD01-B5F8-4B1F-9F4B-863C135926C0` (string (1024), required) - Unique identifier of the partner - the ID is generated during the creation of the partner via API.
+ operatingUnitId: `1A672B37-B674-4F14-A13F-C82EAF53BF15` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the partner's operating unit  - the ID is generated during the creation of the partner's operating unit via API.
+ priority: `100` (integer) - Order's priority, higher number means higher priority of the inserted order. The priority can range from -999 to 999. Even though the element is not mandatory, some number (e.g. constant "0") has to be filled in.
+ dispatchDate: `2021-01-24 00:00:00.000` (datetime) - Scheduled date of dispatch from the warehouse.
+ mergeShipping: `1` (tinyint) - Determines whether it is possible to combine this order incoming together with other orders incoming with the same place of delivery into one shipment. Supported values: 0 - No, 1 - Yes.
+ dispatchIncomplete: `20` (tinyint) - Determines whether it is possible to dispatch an incomplete order incoming. Supported values: `0` - Not specified, `10` - To be confirmed, `20` - Allowed automatically, `25` - Allowed automatically – without repeated picking in case of an issue, `31` - Allowed after correction according to event 28 (Cancels the items that were sent in the event), `40` - Not allowed, `50` - To cancel (Cancels the Order incoming). Value 31 is only available for update (see below).
+ note: `Instructions for packaging` (string(255)) - Note regarding the order incoming. System shows the note in during packaging process on PDA. 
     <i> Formatting options: 
     1) To display multiple separate instructions on the PDA screen, use the enter wildcard character \r\n (there does not need to be a space before or after the character). 
     2) To display different colors for instruction on the PDA screen, use color=\"red\" 
     3) For font size in px, use font size=\"5\". </i>
+ processingMethodCode: `B2C` (string(20)) - Processing method for the inserted order - the code is generated during the creation of the processing method in the WMS. Fill in only if the function for the processing method is switched on in the WMS. <b>Deprecated, use element "processingMethodId".</b>
+ processingMethodId: `B2C` (string(1024)) - Identification of the processing method for the inserted order - the identification is generated during the creation of the processing method in the WMS. Fill in only if the function for the processing method is switched on in the WMS.
+ itemsGroupingMethod: `0` (tinyint) - Method of grouping items of the order incoming. Supported values: 0 - Not specified, 10 - Group items with the same combination of attributes, 20 - Do not group any items.
+ packingListRequired: `0` (tinyint) - Defines whether the packaging list should be printed during dispatch. Supported values: 0 – Do not print, 15 - According to the partner, 20 - Partial - for each logistics unit, 30 - For the order incoming - to the last logistics unit
+ deliveryNoteRequired: `0` (tinyint) - Defines whether the delivery note should be printed during dispatch. Supported values: 0 – Do not print, 15 - According to the partner, 20 - Partial - for each logistics unit, 30 - For the order incoming - to the last logistics unit
+ invoiceRequired: `0` (tinyint) - Defines whether the invoice should be printed during dispatch. Supported values: 0 – Do not print, 15 - According to the partner, 20 - Partial - for each logistics unit, 30 - For the order incoming - to the last logistics unit
+ suspendedLoading: `0` (tinyint) - This element is used to manage suspended loading from the ERP. If loading is suspended, the shipping labels from that order incoming cannot be loaded into the carrier's vehicle until the ERP allows the loading. Supported values: 0 – Not suspended, 10 - Suspended, 20 - Allowed after suspension
+ deliveryMethodCode: `U0001_DPD` (string (20), required) - Delivery method for the inserted order - the code is generated during the creation of the delivery method in the WMS. <b>Deprecated, use element "deliveryMethodId".</b>
+ deliveryMethodId: `U0001_DPD` (string (1024), required) - Identification of the delivery method for the inserted order - the identification is generated during the creation of the delivery method in the WMS.
+ deliveryInstructions: `Shipments are received only between 14:00 and 18:00` (string (255)) - Delivery instructions.
+ deliveryDate: `2025-10-10 00:00:00.000` (datetime) - Delivery date.
+ packagingLevelDefinitionId: `227` (string(1024)) - Definition of the packaging level identification.
+ recipientReference: `DL-22025` (string (255)) - Recipient reference sent to the carrier.
+ primarySystemOrderId: `OC-040925` (string (255)) - Order code from primary system.
+ paymentMethodCode: `COD` (string (20), condition) - Payment method (mandatory only for COD - cash on delivery)  - the code is generated during the creation of the payment method in the WMS. The payment method can be filled in even for the orders without COD, but in that case payment details (variableSymbol, cashAmount, currencyCode) must not be filled in. <b>Deprecated, use element "paymentMethodId".</b>
+ paymentMethodId: `COD` (string (1024), condition) - Identification of the payment method (mandatory only for COD - cash on delivery)  - the identification is generated during the creation of the payment method in the WMS. The identification of the payment method can be filled in even for the orders without COD, but in that case payment details (variableSymbol, cashAmount, currencyCode) must not be filled in.
+ paymentInformation.variableSymbol: `101217896` (string (20), condition) - Variable symbol used for distinguishing the payment (mandatory for COD, otherwise should not be filled in).
+ paymentInformation.cashAmount: `123.5` (numeric (16,5), condition) - Cash amount that should be paid for the inserted order (mandatory for COD, otherwise should not be filled in).
+ paymentInformation.currencyCode: `CZK` (string (3), condition) - Code of currency that should be used for payment (mandatory for COD, otherwise should not be filled in).
+ partyIdentification.company: `KVADOS, a.s.` (string (255)) - Delivery address (B2C) - company name
+ partyIdentification.firstName:  `Pavel` (string (100)) - Delivery address (B2C) - first name of the recipient
+ partyIdentification.lastName: `Novák` (string (200)) - Delivery address (B2C) - second name of the recipient. 
+ partyIdentification.street: `Novoveská 22` (string (100), condition) - Delivery address (B2C) - street. Mandatory if elements "partyIdentification.lastName" or "partyIdentification.company" are filled in.
+ partyIdentification.city: `Ostrava` (string (200), condition) - Delivery address (B2C) - city. Mandatory if elements "partyIdentification.lastName" or "partyIdentification.company" are filled in.
+ partyIdentification.zip: `70900` (string (10), condition) - Delivery address (B2C) - ZIP code. Mandatory if elements "partyIdentification.lastName" or "partyIdentification.company" are filled in.
+ partyIdentification.country: `CZ` (string (40), condition) - Delivery address (B2C) - country. Mandatory if elements "partyIdentification.lastName" or "partyIdentification.company" are filled in. Country code should be filled according to the ISO 3166-1 standard with alpha-2 codes (e.g. "CZ" for Czech Republic).
+ partyIdentification.email: `jan@novak.cz` (string (40), condition) - Delivery address (B2C) - e-mail of the recipient. Mandatory if elements "partyIdentification.lastName" or "partyIdentification.company" are filled in.
+ partyIdentification.phone: `731123456` (string (40), condition) - Delivery address (B2C) - phone number of the recipient. Mandatory if elements "partyIdentification.lastName" or "partyIdentification.company" are filled in.
+ partyIdentification.pickupPlaceCode: `50287` (string (30), condition) - Code of pickup place from the selected carrier's codebook to which the order is to be delivered (B2C). Mandatory if shipment is to be delivered to carrier's pickup place.
+ partyIdentification.externalCarrierCode: `135` (string (60), condition) - Code of the last mile carrier that was chosen for the delivery. Mandatory if shipment is to be delivered by carrier Zásilkovna when delivering abroad.
+ texts.text: `Be careful, fragile items!` (string(32766)) - Text from ERP. Multiple texts can be sent, but only one for each type (element typeOfText).
+ texts.typeOfText: `30` (tinyint) - Type of text. Specifies in which process the text will be displayed. Supported values: 30 - Picking, 40 - Packaging, 50 - Completion, 60 - Loading, 70 - Picking and packaging, 80 - Picking and completion, 90 - Picking, packaging and completion 

+ items.itemCode: `DL-13305/001` (string(40)) - Unique identifier of the order's item (might be arranged for example as "order code/item code"). Each item code should be unique - if this cannot be ensured, it is necessary to use the element "items.extIsId".
+ items.extIsId: `648DC0FF` (string(1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP that must be used when it is not possible to ensure that the value in the element "items.itemCode" is unique. If the identification in the element "items.itemCode" is unique, "items.extIsId" should not be filled in.
+ items.productId: `A770B14D-9E31-427C-9B19-A3D79D3BE8F9` (string (1024), required) - Unique identifier of the product.
+ items.amount.quantity: `7` (numeric (15,4), required) - Quantity of the product (in basic unit of measurement, if there is no other unit of measurement filled in).
+ items.amount.measurementUnitCode: `KS` (string (1024)) - Unit of measurement in which the product is issued from the warehouse - the code is generated during the creation of the unit of measurement in the WMS. If there is no value filled in, system uses the basic unit of measurement for the ordered product.
+ items.warehouseCode: `1` (string (20), condition) - Warehouse code from the ERP valid for the particular item. Fill in only if the attribute "external warehouse" is switched on in the WMS. If the warehouse code is not filled in, WMS works with the warehouse code from the header.
+ items.customerOrderCode: `19274/01` (string (20)) - Partner's order reference from the ERP.
+ items.name: `Dell G5 15 Gaming (5521) Special Edition` (string(222)) - Name of the order incoming's item. If it is not specified, the WMS will automatically use the name of the product.
+ items.commission: `C208211` (string(20)) - The commission code for which the product is issued. Fill in only if the attribute "commission" is switched on in the WMS.
+ items.batch: `LOT220217` (string(100)) - The production batch code of the product which is to be issued from the warehouse. Fill in only if the attribute "batch" is switched on in the WMS.
+ items.batchExt: `LOT_2254` (string(20)) - Batch code recorded in the ERP.
+ items.expirationDate: `2023-09-24` (datetime) - Expiration date of the production batch. Fill in only if the attribute "batch" is switched on in the WMS.
+ items.minExpirationPeriod: `20` (smallint) - Minimum expiration period (in days) from the date of issue/shipment from the warehouse.
+ items.maxExpirationPeriod: `60` (smallint) - Maximum expiration period (in days) from the date of issue/shipment from the warehouse.
+ items.note: `Instructions for picking` (string(255)) - Note regarding the order incoming's item.
+ items.priority: `1` (tinyint) - Priority item. Supported values: 0 – No, 1 - Yes.
+ items.productLabelPrint: `1` (tinyint) - Defines whether the product should be labeled during the packaging. Supported values: 0 - No, 1 - Yes.
+ items.productAssemblyRequired: `1` (tinyint) - Defines whether the product is to be assembled during the packaging. Supported values: 0 - No, 1 - Yes.
+ items.packagingLevelDefinitionId: `335` (string(1024)) - Definition of the packaging level identification on item.
+ items.texts.text: `Be careful, fragile!` (string(32766)) - Text from ERP. Multiple texts can be sent, but only one for each type (element typeOfText).
+ items.texts.typeOfText: `30` (tinyint) - Type of text. Specifies in which process the text will be displayed. Supported values: 30 - Picking, 40 - Packaging, 50 - Completion, 60 - Loading, 70 - Picking and packaging, 80 - Picking and completion, 90 - Picking, packaging and completion 

<b>Extension data</b>

The collection "extensionData" can be added to the web service in order to provide additional elements that are not a part of the standard web service. See the header "Extension data" for more details. The elements labeled as "required" must be filled in only if you want to use the specific extensionData colection.

<b>Extension data – Groups of packaging for shipping</b>

In the WMS, groups of packaging for shipping are recorded in a relational table with a relation to the order incoming.
You can fill in multiple groups in one insert.

+ extensionData.entities.type: `OrderInHeader` (constant, required)
+ extensionData.entities.relations.type: `OrderInPackagingTypeGroup` (constant, required)
+ extensionData.entities.relations.extIsId: `2209231005` (string (1024), required) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP.
+ extensionData.entities.relations.properties.key: `PackagingTypeGroupCode` (constant, required)
+ extensionData.entities.relations.properties.value: `OBL` (string (20)) – The code of the group of packaging for shipping.

### Create an Order incoming [POST /V1/orderIncoming/]

During the creation of an order incoming, the order header is created along with all order items. If an error occurs during the creation of the order incoming, no value (neither header nor order items) is inserted into the WMS database.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "orderCode": "DL-13305",
            "extIsId": "E17C51BF",
            "type": 1,
            "warehouseCode": "1",
            "partnerId": "4D63AD01-B5F8-4B1F-9F4B-863C135926C0",
            "operatingUnitId": "1A672B37-B674-4F14-A13F-C82EAF53BF15",
            "priority": 100,
            "dispatchDate": "2021-01-24 00:00:00.000",
            "mergeShipping": 1,
            "dispatchIncomplete": 20,
            "note": "<font size=\"5\"color=\"red\">Instructions for packaging</font>\r\nSecond instruction",
            "processingMethodId": "B2C",
            "itemsGroupingMethod": 0,
            "packingListRequired": 0,
            "deliveryNoteRequired": 0,
            "invoiceRequired": 0,
            "suspendedLoading": 0,
            "deliveryMethodId": "U0001_DPD",
            "deliveryInstructions": "Shipments are received only between 14:00 and 18:00",
            "deliveryDate": "2025-10-10 00:00:00.000",
            "packagingLevelDefinitionId": "227",
            "recipientReference": "DL-22025",
            "primarySystemOrderId": "OC-040925",
            "paymentMethodId": "COD",
            "paymentInformation": {
                "variableSymbol": "101217896",
                "cashAmount": 123.5,
                "currencyCode": "CZK"
            },
            "partyIdentification": {
                "company": "Kvados, a.s.",
                "firstName": "Pavel",
                "lastName": "Novák",
                "street": "Novoveská 22",
                "city": "Ostrava",
                "zip": "70900",
                "country": "CZ",
                "email": "a@a.cz",
                "phone": "+420558123456",
                "pickupPlaceCode": null,
                "externalCarrierCode": null
            },
            "texts": [
                {
                    "text": "Be careful, fragile items!",
                    "typeOfText": 30
                },
                {
                    "text": "Be careful, fragile items!",
                    "typeOfText": 60
                }
            ],
            "items": [
                {
                    "productId": "A770B14D-9E31-427C-9B19-A3D79D3BE8F9",
                    "amount": {
                        "quantity": 7,
                        "measurementUnitCode": "KS"
                    },
                    "warehouseCode": null,
