### Update an Order incoming [PUT /V1/orderIncoming/{orderIncomingId}]

In order to update an order incoming, it is necessary to send the unique identification (ID) of the order incoming that is to be updated. The body of the web service must include only the elements that should be updated, all the other optional elements should remain null.

Update of an order incoming is only possible until a shipment for the order incoming has been created in the WMS (otherwise the web service will report an error).

If it is requested to update an item, the item’s identification (element "itemId") must be filled in.

In order to cancel an item of the order incoming, it is sufficient to update its quantity to zero. If it is requested to cancel the whole order incoming, it is necessary to use different web service (see the part "Delete an Order incoming").

In order to add a new item to the order incoming, it is necessary to send the item without the element "itemId" filled in (when the "itemId" is filled in, the web service tries to update that item). When adding a new item, all the required information for that item (see the part "Create an Order incoming") must be filled in.

List of elements that may be updated:
+ partnerId: `4D63AD01-B5F8-4B1F-9F4B-863C135926C0` (string (1024))
+ operatingUnitId: `1A672B37-B674-4F14-A13F-C82EAF53BF15` (string (1024))
+ priority: `100` (integer)
+ dispatchDate: `2021-01-24 00:00:00.000` (datetime)
+ mergeShipping: `1` (tinyint)
+ dispatchIncomplete: `20` (tinyint) - Values: `0` - Not specified, `10` - To be confirmed, `20` - Allowed automatically, `40` - Not allowed, can only be sent as an update until a shipment for the order incoming has been created in the WMS. Values: `31` - Allowed after correction according to event 28 (Cancels the items that were reported in the event 28 - in this case, it is also allowed to replace a missing item with a new item or increase quantity of one of the existing items during the update), `50` - To cancel (Cancels the Order incoming), can be sent as an update only if the current value of the element "dispatchIncomplete" is `10` - To be confirmed.
+ note: `Instructions for packaging` (string(255))
+ suspendedLoading: `0` (tinyint) - Element can be updated at any time, regardless of the status of the shipment.
+ processingMethodCode: `B2C` (string(20))
+ processingMethodId: `B2C` (string(1024))
+ deliveryMethodCode: `U0001_DPD` (string (20))
+ deliveryMethodId: `U0001_DPD` (string (1024))
+ deliveryInstructions: `Shipments are received only between 14:00 and 18:00` (string (255)) - Element can be updated at any time, regardless of the status of the shipment.
+ deliveryDate: `2025-10-10 00:00:00.000` (datetime)
+ packagingLevelDefinitionId: `227` (string(1024))
+ recipientReference: `DL-22025` (string (255))
+ primarySystemOrderId: `OC-040925` (string (255))
+ paymentMethodCode: `COD` (string (20))
+ paymentMethodId: `COD` (string (1024))
+ paymentInformation.variableSymbol: `101217896` (string (20))
+ paymentInformation.cashAmount: `123.5` (numeric (16,5))
+ partyIdentification.company: `KVADOS, a.s.` (string (255))
+ partyIdentification.firstName:  `Pavel` (string (100))
+ partyIdentification.lastName: `Novák` (string (200))
+ partyIdentification.street: `Novoveská 22` (string (100))
+ partyIdentification.city: `Ostrava` (string (200))
+ partyIdentification.zip: `70900` (string (10))
+ partyIdentification.country: `CZ` (string (40))
+ partyIdentification.email: `jan@novak.cz` (string (40))
+ partyIdentification.phone: `731123456` (string (40))
+ partyIdentification.pickupPlaceCode: `50287` (string (30))
+ partyIdentification.externalCarrierCode: `135` (string (60))
+ texts.text: `Be careful, fragile items!` (string(32766)) - If it is sent with an empty string, the text is deleted in the WMS. If multiple texts were sent via insert, the type (element typeOfText) for which we want to change or delete the text must also be specified during the update.

+ items.itemId: `688D16D6-BF90-4E50-B84B-053F52AE7224` (string (1024)) – Not eligible for update, itemId is used only for identification of the item that is to be updated.
+ items.amount.quantity: `7` (numeric (15,4))
+ items.amount.measurementUnitCode: `KS` (string (1024))
+ items.customerOrderCode: `19274/01` (string (20))
+ items.note: `Instructions for picking` (string(255))
+ items.batchExt: `LOT_2254` (string(20))
+ items.priority: `1` (tinyint)
+ items.minExpirationPeriod: `20` (smallint)
+ items.maxExpirationPeriod: `60` (smallint)
+ items.packagingLevelDefinitionId: `335` (string(1024))
+ items.texts.text: `Be careful, fragile!` (string(32766)) - If it is sent with an empty string, the text is deleted in the WMS. If multiple texts were sent via insert, the type (element typeOfText) for which we want to change or delete the text must also be specified during the update.

+ Parameters
    + orderIncomingId: `5DC73A08-AC06-4B24-BFAF-32DE2E42A102` (string) - A unique identifier of the order incoming you want to update.

+ Request (application/json)

