### Delete an Order incoming [DELETE /V1/orderIncoming/{orderIncomingId}]

In order to cancel an order incoming, it is necessary to send the unique identification (ID) of the order incoming that is to be cancelled. The result is the cancellation of the entire order incoming and all its items.

Cancellation of an order incoming is only possible until the processing of the shipment for the order incoming has started in the WMS (otherwise the web service will report an error).

+ Parameters
    + orderIncomingId: `5DC73A08-AC06-4B24-BFAF-32DE2E42A102` (string, required) - A unique identifier of the order incoming you want to cancel.

+ Request (application/json)

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
        "data": "OK",
        "errors": []
        }
        
+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
        "data": null,
        "errors": [
            {
                "errorText": "Invalid entry",
                "errorType": 3,
                "internalRecordId": null,
                "propertyName": "id",
                "recordId": "0",
                "recordType": "orderIncoming",
                "sourceId": null
            }
            ]
        }

## Order incoming processing [/V1/orderIncomingProcessing/]
Base URI template that is used at the end of the URL when the web service is called: <b>/V1/orderIncomingProcessing/</b> (example: https://demo.mystock.cz/V1/orderIncomingProcessing/).

This web service is used to "lock" an order incoming if the order is in a status that prevents updates via the standard method (the /V1/orderIncoming/ service). Once the service is invoked and the order is "locked," it is then possible - for specific use cases - to update the order incoming (via the /V1/orderIncoming/ service) and then "unlock" the order by calling the service again. While the order is "locked," it cannot be processed within the WMS processes.

Currently supported use cases:
1) Changing the delivery method if a shipment for the order incoming already exists in the WMS.

### Setting the lock [POST /V1/orderIncomingProcessing/{orderIncomingId}/{suspensionType}]

The web service has following parameters:
+ orderIncomingId: `45790E69-2EED-4D10-8DA7-E25C2486F4BC` (string (1024), required) - Unique identifier of the order incoming for which the lock is to be set due to a delivery method update on the order incoming/shipment.

Subsequently, it is necessary to select one parameter for the reason for suspending the document.
+ SuspensionShippingConsignmentGenerationSet - Suspension type = Shipment generation suspension. If no shipment exists, it is possible to update values on the order incoming in the standard way.
+ SuspensionPackingSet - Suspension type = Packing suspension. If a document lock is set on the order incoming, updating the delivery method is permitted, provided that the shipment packing has not yet started.
+ SuspensionCompletionSet - Suspension type = Completion suspension. If a document lock is set on the order incoming, updating the delivery method is permitted, provided that the shipment completion has not yet started.

Each displayed result has following elements:
+ lockId: `4BB8642B-6EA8-4E60-AC0F-E4BC1A0ABF15` (string (1024)) - ID of the lock that was generated by the API when the lock record was created.

+ Parameters
    + orderIncomingId: `45790E69-2EED-4D10-8DA7-E25C2486F4BC` (string (1024), required) - Unique identifier of the order incoming.
    + SuspensionShippingConsignmentGenerationSet - Select only one parameter for the reason for suspending the document.
    + SuspensionPackingSet - Select only one parameter for the reason for suspending the document.
    + SuspensionCompletionSet - Select only one parameter for the reason for suspending the document.

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "errors": [],
            "data": {
                "lockId": "9E7D9A9C-9781-45B8-B108-D61E96B1C146"
            }
        }

+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
            "errors": [
                {
                    "errorText": "The packing process has started for order DK0707202258 (10OP22500000571)."
                }
            ],
            "data": null
        }

### Deactivating  the lock [POST /V1/orderIncomingProcessing/{orderIncomingId}/{suspensionType}{?lockId}]

The web service has following parameters:
+ orderIncomingId: `45790E69-2EED-4D10-8DA7-E25C2486F4BC` (string (1024), required) - Unique identifier of the order incoming for which the lock is to be deactivated.
+ lockId: `9E7D9A9C-9781-45B8-B108-D61E96B1C146` (string (1024), required) - ID of the lock that was generated by the API when the lock record was created.

When deactivating a lock, it is necessary to select a single parameter that matches the suspension type of the lock being reset.
+ SuspensionShippingConsignmentGenerationReset - Suspension type = Shipment generation suspension.
+ SuspensionPackingReset - Suspension type = Packing suspension.
+ SuspensionCompletionReset - Suspension type = Completion suspension.

Each displayed result has following elements:
+ lockId: `9E7D9A9C-9781-45B8-B108-D61E96B1C146` (string (1024)) - ID of the lock that was generated by the API when the lock record was created.

+ Parameters
    + orderIncomingId: `45790E69-2EED-4D10-8DA7-E25C2486F4BC` (string (1024), required) - Unique identifier of the order incoming.
    + SuspensionShippingConsignmentGenerationReset - Select a single parameter that matches the suspension type of the lock being reset.
    + SuspensionPackingReset - Select a single parameter that matches the suspension type of the lock being reset.
    + SuspensionCompletionReset - Select a single parameter that matches the suspension type of the lock being reset.
    + lockId: `9E7D9A9C-9781-45B8-B108-D61E96B1C146` (string (1024), required)

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "errors": [],
            "data": {
                "lockId": "9E7D9A9C-9781-45B8-B108-D61E96B1C146"
            }
        }

## Issue [/V1/issue/]

Base URI template that is used at the end of the URL when the web service is called: <b>/V1/issue/</b> (example: https://demo.mystock.cz/V1/issue/).

The web service has following elements:
+ issueCode: `IC55458` (string (20), required) - Issue code from the ERP system. Each issue code should be unique - if this cannot be ensured, it is necessary to use the element "extIsId".
+ extIsId: `D77F6803` (string(1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP that must be used when it is not possible to ensure that the value in the element "issueCode" is unique. If the identification in the element "issueCode" is unique, "extIsId" should not be filled in.
+ issueDate: `2023-05-09 00:00:00.000` (datetime, required) - Scheduled date of issue, according to which the priority of tasks for issue will be set in the WMS.
+ type: `0 ` (tinyint, required) - Supported issue types: 0 - internal, 1 – external. It is also possible to send a user-defined value. The allowable range is 90000 - 99999. A user-defined value can be combined with an element "specification".
+ warehouseCode: `1001` (string(20), condition) - Warehouse code from the ERP.
+ centerCode: `10` (string(20), condition) - Center code - must be filled in only for the internal issues, the element should not be filled in for the other issue types.
+ partnerId: `21CF6041-BE1C-4503-9CE8-68D969B4E786` (string(1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the partner - ID will be generated during the creation of partner via API.
+ operatingUnitId: `365708E1-3E9C-46B9-B7AF-6F5D5063E8E2` (string(1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the partner's operating unit  - ID will be generated during the creation of partner's operating unit via API. The element is filled in only for the external issues - if the element is not filled in, an operating unit with the code ""CEN"" is used for the external issue. For other types of issues the element may remain null.
+ note: `Note of the issue ` (string(255)) - Note regarding the issue.
+ processImmediately: `0` (tinyint) - Issue note will be finished after successful import into WMS. Automatically start subsequent processes on the WMS side. Supported values: 0 - No, 1 – Yes.
+ specification: `SPEC_01` (string (20)) - Specification of the issue.

+ items.itemCode: `VD_POL_001` (string(40)) - Unique identifier of the issue's item. Each item code should be unique - if this cannot be ensured, it is necessary to use the element "items.extIsId".
+ items.extIsId: `2EDC6076` (string(1024), condition) – Unique identifier of the record in the ERP that must be used when it is not possible to ensure that the value in the element "items.itemCode" is unique. If the identification in the element "items.itemCode" is unique, "items.extIsId" should not be filled in.
+ items.productId: `B587A515-1BF0-46A9-8166-9319FD962C2D` (string(1024), required) - Unique identifier of the product. For internal issues you can use same values for multiple items.
+ items.name: `Dell G5 15 Gaming (5521) Special Edition` (string(222)) - Name of the issue's item. If it is not specified, the WMS will automatically use the name of the product.
+ items.locationCode: `ASSEMBLY` (string(20)) - WMS Location code used for internal product issue from the warehouse. The element is used only for the internal issue notes. For example: issue to production, issue for warranty claims, goods disposal, etc.
+ items.batch: `LOT220217` (string(100)) - The production batch code of the product which is issued from the warehouse. For internal issues you can use same values for multiple items.
+ items.batchExt: `LOT_2254` (string(20)) - Batch code recorded in the ERP.
+ items.expirationDate: `2023-09-24` (datetime) - Expiration date of the production batch. For internal issues you can use same values for multiple items.
+ items.countryOfOriginId: `CZ` (string(3)) - Country of origin code.
+ items.variant: `RIGHT` (string(20)) – Variant code.
+ items.commission: `C208211` (string(20)) - The commission code for which the product is issued from the warehouse. Element is used only in case of issue for specific commission.
+ items.correctedDocumentId: `ADA11CBB-8E63-4C17-AB9A-6B83E54BC56B` (string(1024)) - Primary header document (used for correction documents).
+ items.correctedItemId: `23F3A544-A7D3-462B-947D-AF3CCD1BD29B` (string(1024)) - Primary item (used for correction documents).
+ items.note: `Note of the item` (string(255)) - Note regarding the issue's item.
+ items.amount.quantity: `5` (numeric(15,4)) - Quantity of product in the purchase unit of measurement (unless another unit of measurement is filled in).
+ items.amount.measurementUnitCode: `KS` (string(1024)) - Unit of measurement in which the product is issued from the warehouse - code will be generated during the creation of unit of measurement in the WMS. If the element is not filled in, the WMS uses the basic unit of measurement for the ordered product.
+ items.qualityId: `DCE838E1-5A27-48EF-9746-7E1C62791776` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the quality. A property of the stock card that defines the level of its quality. (filled in only if the quality is being recorded and the attribute "quality" is switched on in the WMS)

### Create an Issue [POST /V1/issue/]

During the creation of an issue, the issue header is created along with all its items, if they are filled in. If an error occurs during the creation of the issue, no value (neither header nor items) is inserted into the WMS database.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "issueCode": "IC55458",
            "issueDate": "2023-05-09 00:00:00.000",
            "extIsId": "D77F6803",
            "type": 0,
            "warehouseCode": "1001",
            "centerCode": "10",
