+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
          "data": null,
          "errors": [
            {
              "errorText": "The entered value is NULL",
              "errorType": 1,
              "internalRecordId": null,
              "propertyName": "productId",
              "recordId": "1",
              "recordType": "issue",
              "sourceId": "D77F6803"
            }
          ]
        }

## Shipping label [/V1/shippingLabel/]

Base URI template that is used at the end of the URL when the web service is called: <b>/V1/shippingLabel/</b> (example: https://demo.mystock.cz/V1/shippingLabel/).

The web service has following elements:
+ shippingLabelCode: `40812169424` (string (255), required) - The shipping label code printed on the label of the carrier. Each shipping label code must be unique.
+ extIsId: `648DC0FF` (string(1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP.
+ deliveryMethodCode: `DPD_CZ` (string (20), required) - Delivery method for the inserted order - the code is generated during the creation of the delivery method in the WMS. <b>Deprecated, use element "deliveryMethodId".</b>
+ deliveryMethodId: `DPD_CZ` (string (1024), required) - Identification of the delivery method - the identification is generated during the creation of the delivery method in the WMS.
+ logisticUnitCode: `ESHOP0000002160` (string (35), required) - Logistics unit code. The value is sent to the ERP in event 26 in the logisticUnitCode element.
+ shippingLabelSyntaxType: `10` (tinyint) – The syntax type of the shipping label. If it is not specified, the WMS will use the value 10. Supported values:
<br>10 - PDF encoded in Base64</br>
<br>20 - ZPL encoded in Base64</br>
+ shippingLabelSyntax: `` (string (32766), required) - Syntax of the shipping label from the ERP.

### Create a Shipping label [POST /V1/shippingLabel/]
When a logistic unit is created, a transport label is created for the logistic unit specified in the logisticUnitCode element.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "shippingLabelCode": "40812169424",
            "extIsId": "648DC0FF",
            "deliveryMethodId": "DPD_CZ",
            "logisticUnitCode": "ESHOP0000002160",
            "shippingLabelSyntaxType": 10,
            "shippingLabelSyntax": ""
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
            "errors": [],
            "data": {
                "ids": [
                    {
                        "id": "5DAE57FC-30E0-4FE3-87B6-2F7B1F83E573",
                        "recordId": "1",
                        "sourceId": "648DC0FF",
                        "type": "shippingLabel"
                    }
                ]
            }
        }
                
+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
            "errors": [
                {
                    "errorType": 3,
                    "errorText": "Invalid entry",
                    "sourceId": "648DC0FF",
                    "recordId": "0",
                    "recordType": "shippingLabel",
                    "propertyName": "deliveryMethodCode"
                }
            ],
            "data": null
        }

### Update a Shipping label [PUT /V1/shippingLabel/{shippingLabelId}]
In the update web service, it is always necessary to send a unique identification of the changed record (ID) in the URL. The body of the update web service should contain only those elements that need to be changed.

If one of the updated values is filled in incorrectly and the validation procedure reports an error, the system will cancel the whole update - none of the changed values will be updated.

Update of a shipping label is only possible until the shipping label is printed and paired with the logistics unit.

List of elements that may be updated:
+ shippingLabelCode: `40812169424` (string (255))
+ shippingLabelSyntax: `^XA^MUD^CI28^CW0,TT0003M_.FNT^LH0,0^FO17,17^GB750,1139,3^FS^FO17,17^GB221,469,1^FS^FO67,101^BY3^BCB,121,N,N,N,A^FDZ3185290768^FS^FT224,385^A0B,34^FDZ 318 5290 768^FS^FO238,17^GB154,469,1^FS^FT342,436^A0B,47^FDZasilkovna.cz^FS^FT342,435^A0B,47^FDZasilkovna.cz^FS^FT342,434^A0B,47^FDZasilkovna.cz^FS^FO392,17^GB375,759,1^FS^FT488,726^A0B,27^FDPrijemce^FS^FT533,726^A0B,34^FDJan Novak^FS^FT533,725^A0B,34^FDFDNote: ^FS^FO392,776^GB375,379,1^FS^XZ` (string (32766)) 
+ shippingLabelSyntaxType: `20` (tinyint, condition) - Mandatory if the element "shippingLabelSyntax" is filled in and label syntax is ZPL, otherwise should not be filled in.

+ Parameters
    + shippingLabelId: `4D63AD01-B5F8-4B1F-9F4B-863C135926C0` (string) - A unique identifier of the shipping label you want to update.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "shippingLabelCode": "40812169424",
            "shippingLabelSyntaxType": "20",
            "shippingLabelSyntax": "^XA^MUD^CI28^CW0,TT0003M_.FNT^LH0,0^FO17,17^GB750,1139,3^FS^FO17,17^GB221,469,1^FS^FO67,101^BY3^BCB,121,N,N,N,A^FDZ3185290768^FS^FT224,385^A0B,34^FDZ 318 5290 768^FS^FO238,17^GB154,469,1^FS^FT342,436^A0B,47^FDZasilkovna.cz^FS^FT342,435^A0B,47^FDZasilkovna.cz^FS^FT342,434^A0B,47^FDZasilkovna.cz^FS^FO392,17^GB375,759,1^FS^FT488,726^A0B,27^FDPrijemce^FS^FT533,726^A0B,34^FDJan Novak^FS^FT533,725^A0B,34^FDFDNote: ^FS^FO392,776^GB375,379,1^FS^XZ"
        }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
        "data": "OK",
        "errors": []
        }
        
+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
            "errors": [
                {
                    "errorType": 6,
                    "errorText": "Update is not permitted",
                    "recordId": "0",
                    "recordType": "shippingLabel",
                    "propertyName": "id"
                }
            ],
            "data": null
        }

### Delete a Shipping label [DELETE /V1/shippingLabel/{shippingLabelId}]

In order to cancel a shipping label, it is necessary to send the unique identification (ID) of the shipping labek that is to be cancelled. The result is the cancellation of the entire shipping label.

Cancellation of a shipping label is only possible until the shipping label is printed and paired with the logistics unit.

+ Parameters
    + shippingLabelId: `5DC73A08-AC06-4B24-BFAF-32DE2E42A102` (string, required) - A unique identifier of the shipping label you want to cancel

+ Request (application/json)

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
        "data": "OK",
        "errors": []
        }
        
+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
            "errors": [
                {
                    "errorType": 3,
                    "errorText": "Invalid entry",
                    "recordId": "0",
                    "recordType": "shippingLabel",
                    "propertyName": "id"
                }
            ],
            "data": null
        }

## Warehouse transfer [/V1/warehouseTransfer/]
This web service is <b>deprecated</b>, replaced by web service "inventoryTransferRequest".

Base URI template that is used at the end of the URL when the web service is called: <b>/V1/warehouseTransfer/</b> (example: https://demo.mystock.cz/V1/warehouseTransfer/).

The web service has following elements:
+ transferCode: `VZ210924001` (string (20), required) - Tranfer code from the ERP system. Each transfer code should be unique - if this cannot be ensured, it is necessary to use the element "extIsId". 
+ extIsId: `352C7B30` (string(1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP that must be used when it is not possible to ensure that the value in the element "transferCode" is unique. If the identification in the element "transferCode" is unique, "extIsId" should not be filled in.
+ note: `Note of the warehouse transfer` (string(255)) - Note regarding the warehouse transfer.
+ processImmediately: `0` (tinyint) - Automatically start subsequent processes on the WMS side. Supported values: 0 - No, 1 – Yes.
+ productId: `76C15706-9604-4CE8-A8DE-65EB62492F49` (string(1024), required) - Unique identifier of the product.
+ locationCode: `ASSEMBLY` (string(20)) - WMS Location code used for warehouse transfer.
+ commission: `C208211` (string(40)) - The commission code for which the product is transfered between warehouses.
+ batch: `LOT220217` (string(100)) - The production batch code under which the product is transfered between warehouses.
+ expirationDate: `2023-09-24` (datetime) - Expiration date of the production batch.
+ variant: `RIGHT` (string(100)) – Variant code.
+ countryOfOriginId: `D9F3A61E-46A6-425B-A26E-D76CDEFC2AC8` (string(1024)) - Unique identifier of the country of origin.
+ warehouseCodeFrom: `3S20` (string(20), required) - Default warehouse code.
+ warehouseCodeTo: `3S20A` (string(20), required) - Destination warehouse code
+ amount.measurementUnitCode: `KS` (string(1024), required) - Unit of measurement in which the product is transfered - code will be generated during the creation of unit of measurement in the WMS. If the element is not filled in, the WMS uses the basic unit of measurement for the ordered product.
+ amount.quantity: `5` (numeric(15,4), required) - Quantity of product in the purchase unit of measurement (unless another unit of measurement is filled in).

### Create a Warehouse transfer [POST /V1/warehouseTransfer/]

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "transferCode": "VZ210924001",
            "extIsId": "352C7B30",
            "note": "Note of the warehouse transfer",
            "processImmediately": 0,
            "productId": "76C15706-9604-4CE8-A8DE-65EB62492F49",
            "locationCode": "ASSEMBLY",
            "commission": "C208211",
            "batch": "LOT220217",
            "expirationDate": "2023-09-24",
            "variant": "RIGHT",
            "countryOfOriginId": "D9F3A61E-46A6-425B-A26E-D76CDEFC2AC8",
            "warehouseCodeFrom": "3S20",
            "warehouseCodeTo": "3S20A",
            "amount": {
                "measurementUnitCode": "KS",
                "quantity": 5
            }
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
          "errors": [],
          "data": {
            "ids": [
              {
                "id": "5DAE57FC-30E0-4FE3-87B6-2F7B1F83E573",
                "recordId": "1",
                "sourceId": "352C7B30",
                "type": "warehouseTransfer"
              }
            ]
          }
        }
               
+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
          "data": null,
          "errors": [
            {
              "errorText": "The entered value is NULL",
              "errorType": 1,
              "internalRecordId": null,
              "propertyName": "productId",
              "recordId": "1",
              "recordType": "warehouseTransfer",
              "sourceId": "352C7B30"
            }
          ]
        }

## Inventory transfer request [/V1/inventoryTransferRequest/]
Base URI template that is used at the end of the URL when the web service is called: <b>/V1/inventoryTransferRequest/</b> (example: https://demo.mystock.cz/V1/inventoryTransferRequest/).

The web service has following elements:
+ requestCode: `REQ_2023/02-103021` (string (20), required) – Request code from the ERP system. Each request code should be unique - if this cannot be ensured, it is necessary to use the element "extIsId".
+ extIsId: `ID_260523` (string(1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP that must be used when it is not possible to ensure that the value in the element "requestCode" is unique. If the identification in the element "requestCode" is unique, "extIsId" should not be filled in.
+ processOnlyInWhole: `0` (tinyint) – Process only in whole. Supported values: `0` - No, `1` - Yes (The system will cancel the request if it is not possible to generate tasks for all items within the Inventory Transfer Request header).
+ taskGenerationDate: `2023-05-09 01:00:00.00` (datetime) - On the date and time specified, the system will attempt to generate Inventory Transfer Requests from the child IT requests. The date and time must be greater than the current date. Enter the date in the format e.g. 2019-05-09 00:00:00.000.
+ startProcValidityDate: `2023-05-09 22:00:00.00` (datetime) - If the processing of Inventory Transfer Requests has not started by the specified date and time, the system will cancel the requests. If value is absent, the check is not performed. The date and time must be greater than the current date. Enter the date in the format e.g. 2019-05-09 00:00:00.000.
+ note: `Vyprázdnění všech BINů (nosičů v AutoStore) typu "CeloBIN".` (string(255)) - Note regarding the Requirements to optimize stock location.

+ items.itemCode: `REQ_ITEM_001.1` (string (40), condition) - Unique identifier of the requirement´s item. Each item code should be unique - if this cannot be ensured, it is necessary to use the element "items.extIsId".
+ items.extIsId: `ID_260523` (string(1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP that must be used when it is not possible to ensure that the value in the element "items.itemCode" is unique. If the identification in the element "items.itemCode" is unique, "items.extIsId" should not be filled in.
+ items.productId: `C4EB6639-AA11-4610-BA9E-66691E35EEC7` (string(1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the product. Element is mandatory if the element "items.locationCodeFrom" is not filled.
+ items.quantity.quantity: `1` (numeric (15,4), condition) - Quantity of product (in basic unit of measurement). Element is mandatory if the element "items.wholeAvailableQuantity" is not specified or 0.
+ items.quantity.measurementUnitCode: `pcs` (string (1024)) - Unit of measure quantity of the product to be transfer. - ID will be generated during the creation of unit of measurement in the WMS. If this box is empty, system uses the basic unit of measurement for the product.
+ items.wholeAvailableQuantity: `1` (tinyint, condition) - Process the whole available quantity of the product in location/section/stock (if specified). Supported values: `0` - No, `1` - Yes. Element is mandatory if the element "items.quantity.quantity" is not specified or 0.

+ items.warehouseCodeFrom: `3S20` (string (20), required) - The code of source stock, from which the transfer of the product is requested.
+ items.warehouseCodeTo: `3S20D` (string (20)) - The code of destination stock, to which the transfer of the product is requested.
+ items.sectionCodeFrom: `AS` (string (1024)) - The unique identifier of the source section, from which the transfer of the product is requested. The section code of the stock is generated at mySTOCK WMS server. The creation of a section is not imported through API.
+ items.sectionCodeTo: `PS` (string (1024), condition) - The unique identifier of the target section, to which the transfer of the product is requested. The section code of the stock is generated at mySTOCK WMS server. The creation of a section is not imported through API. Element is mandatory if the element "items.locationCodeTo" is not filled.
+ items.locationCodeFrom: `AS102851_1` (string (20), condition) - The code of the source location in the WMS where the transfer of the product is requested. Element is mandatory if the element "items.productId" is not filled.
+ items.locationCodeTo: `PS01-05-01-00` (string (20), condition) - The code of the target location in the WMS where the transfer of the product is requested. Element is mandatory if the element "items.sectionCodeTo" is not filled.
+ items.commission: `9ZTGNP` (string(40)) - Commission number of the product (filled in only if the product was manufactured/received for certain commission and the attribute "commission" is switched on in the WMS).
+ items.commissionTo: `65TA51` (string(40)) - New commission number of the product.
+ items.batch: `LOT220217` (string(100)) - The production batch code of the product. Fill in only if the attribute "batch" is switched on in the WMS.
+ items.batchExt: `LOT_2254` (string(20)) - Batch code recorded in the ERP.

### Create an Inventory tranfer request [POST /V1/inventoryTransferRequest/]
During the creation of an Inventory transfer request,  the inventory transfer header is created along with all its items. If an error occurs during the creation of the Inventory transfer request, no value (neither header nor items) is inserted into the WMS database.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "extIsId": "ID_260523",
            "requestCode": "REQ_2023/02-103021",
            "processOnlyInWhole": 0,
            "taskGenerationDate": "2023-05-09 01:00:00.00",
            "startProcValidityDate": "2023-05-09 22:00:00.00",
            "note": "Vyprázdnění všech BINů typu CeloBIN.",
            "items": [
                {
                    "extIsId": "ID_260523/item01",
                    "itemCode": "REQ_ITEM_001.1",
                    "productId": "C4EB6639-AA11-4610-BA9E-66691E35EEC7",
                    "wholeAvailableQuantity": 1,
                    "warehouseCodeFrom": "3S20",
                    "warehouseCodeTo": "3S20D",
                    "sectionCodeFrom": "AS",
                    "sectionCodeTo": "PS",
                    "locationCodeFrom": "AS102851_1",
                    "locationCodeTo": "PS01-05-01-00",
                    "commission": "9ZTGNP",
                    "commissionTo": "65TA51",
                    "batch": "LOT220217",
                    "batchExt": "LOT_2254"
                },
                {
                    "extIsId": "ID_260523/item02",
                    "itemCode": "REQ_ITEM_001.2",
                    "productId": "84251544-1E80-4B03-AEE5-F6DDA1577E65",
                    "quantity": {
                        "quantity": 1.000000,
                        "measurementUnitCode": "pcs"
                    },
                    "wholeAvailableQuantity": 0,
                    "warehouseCodeFrom": "3S20",
                    "warehouseCodeTo": "3S20",
                    "locationCodeFrom": "AS102851_1",
                    "locationCodeTo": "AS312251_4"
                }
            ]
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
            "errors": [],
            "data": {
                "ids": [
                    {
                        "id": "0AA01E57-236A-4448-A630-99D7C765363A",
                        "recordId": "0",
                        "sourceId": "ID_260523",
                        "type": "inventoryTransferRequest"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "BEBA2306-35DB-42C6-A87B-A033DBEC2A07",
                        "recordId": "1",
                        "sourceId": "ID_260523/item01",
                        "type": "inventoryTransferRequestItem"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "722FA49D-8E3A-4A69-A1E5-F30843CF5FA1",
                        "recordId": "2",
                        "sourceId": "ID_260523/item02",
                        "type": "inventoryTransferRequestItem"
                    }
                ]
            }
        }
               
+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
            "data": null,
            "errors": [
                {
                    "errorType": 3,
                    "errorText": "Invalid entry",
                    "sourceId": "ID_260523",
                    "recordId": "1",
                    "recordType": "inventoryTransferRequest",
                    "propertyName": "items.productId"
                }
            ]
        }

### Update an Inventory transfer request [PUT /V1/inventoryTransferRequest/{inventoryTransferRequestId}]
In the update web service, it is always necessary to send a unique identification of the changed record (ID) in the URL. The body of the update web service should contain only those elements that need to be changed (e.g. if you only need to change requirement´s item quantity, all the other optional elements should remain null).

Update of the Inventory Transfer Request header or creation of a new item is only possible until the generation of tasks from the Inventory Transfer Request items begins.

Update of the Inventory Transfer Request items is only possible until the generation of tasks from the given item begins.

If it is requested to update an item, the item’s identification (element "itemId") must be filled in.

In order to cancel an item of the Inventory transfer request, it is sufficient to update its quantity and whole available quantity to zero. If it is requested to cancel the whole Inventory transfer request, it is necessary to use different web service (see the part "Delete an Inventory transfer request“).

If the item has elements "items.quantity.quantity" = 0 and "items.wholeAvailableQuantity" = 0, tasks are not generated.

In order to add a new item to the Inventory transfer request, it is necessary to send the item without the element "itemId" filled in (when the "itemId" is filled in, the web service tries to update that item). When adding a new item, all the required information for that item (see the part "Create an Inventory Transfer Request") must be filled in.

If one of the updated values is filled in incorrectly and the validation procedure reports an error, the system will cancel the whole update - none of the changed values will be updated.

List of elements that may be updated:
+ processOnlyInWhole: `0` (tinyint)
+ taskGenerationDate: `2023-05-09 01:00:00.00` (datetime)
+ startProcValidityDate: `2023-05-09 22:00:00.00` (datetime)
+ note: `Vyprázdnění všech BINů (nosičů v AutoStore) typu "CeloBIN".` (string(255))

+ items.itemId: `688D16D6-BF90-4E50-B84B-053F52AE7224` (string (1024)) – Not eligible for update, itemId is used only for identification of the item that is to be updated.
+ items.quantity.quantity: `1` (numeric (15,4))
+ items.quantity.measurementUnitCode: `pcs` (string (1024))
+ items.wholeAvailableQuantity: `1` (tinyint)

+ Parameters
    + inventoryTransferRequestId: `4D63AD01-B5F8-4B1F-9F4B-863C135926C0` (string) - A unique identifier of the inventory transfer request you want to update.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "processOnlyInWhole": 1,
            "taskGenerationDate": "2023-06-30T00:00:00",
            "startProcValidityDate": "2023-06-30T00:00:00",
            "note": "poznamka",
            "items": [
                {
                    "itemId": "688D16D6-BF90-4E50-B84B-053F52AE7224",
                    "quantity": {
                        "quantity": 1.000000,
                        "measurementUnitCode": "pcs"
                    },
                    "wholeAvailableQuantity": 0
                },
                {
                    "extIsId": "648DC0FF",
                    "itemCode": "REQ_ITEM_001.1",
                    "productId": "84251544-1E80-4B03-AEE5-F6DDA1577E65",
                    "wholeAvailableQuantity": 1,
                    "warehouseCodeFrom": "3S20",
                    "warehouseCodeTo": "3S20D",
                    "sectionCodeFrom": "AS",
                    "sectionCodeTo": "PS",
                    "locationCodeFrom": "AS102851_1",
                    "locationCodeTo": "PS01-05-01-00"
                }
            ]
        }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
          "errors": [],
          "data": {
            "ids": [
              {
                "id": "5A5D47AD-AC98-406A-9FBA-CEF21FEEE03F",
                "recordId": "1",
                "sourceId": "648DC0FF",
                "type": "inventoryTransferRequestItem"
              }
            ]
          }
        }
        
+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
            "errors": [
                {
                    "errorType": 4,
                    "errorText": "Selected order cannot be updated, it is being processed",
                    "sourceId": "ITR_0001",
                    "recordId": "0",
                    "recordType": "inventoryTransferRequest",
                    "propertyName": "id",
                    "internalRecordId": ""
                }
            ],
            "data": null
        }
        
### Delete an Inventory transfer request [DELETE /V1/inventoryTransferRequest/{inventoryTransferRequestId}]
In order to cancel an inventory transfer request, it is necessary to send the unique identification (ID) of the inventory transfer request that is to be cancelled. The result is the cancellation of the entire inventory transfer request and all its items.

Delete of the Inventory Transfer Request header is only possible until the generation of tasks from the Inventory Transfer Request items begins.

+ Parameters
    + inventoryTransferRequestId: `4D63AD01-B5F8-4B1F-9F4B-863C135926C0` (string, required) - A unique identifier of the inventory transfer request you want to cancel.

+ Request (application/json)

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
        "data": "OK",
        "errors": []
        }
        
+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
        "data": null,
        "errors": [
            {
                "errorText": "Invalid entry",
                "errorType": 3,
                "internalRecordId": null,
                "propertyName": "id",
                "recordId": "0",
                "recordType": "inventoryTransferRequest",
                "sourceId": null
            }
            ]
        }
        
## Issue to production [/V1/issueToProduction/]
Base URI template that is used at the end of the URL when the web service is called: <b>/V1/issueToProduction/</b> (example: https://demo.mystock.cz/V1/issueToProduction/).

This web service is used when some product has to be issued to production (e.g. the product is transferred to some location in front of the machine from where it is consumed.

The web service has following elements:
+ productionOrderCode: `VP007024` (string (20), required) - Production order code from the ERP system. Each production order code should be unique - if this cannot be ensured, it is necessary to use the element "extIsId".
+ extIsId: `2ADEAC8D` (string (1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP that must be used when it is not possible to ensure that the value in the element "productionOrderCode" is unique. If the identification in the element "productionOrderCode" is unique, "extIsId" should not be filled in.
+ productionDate: `2022-05-21 14:50:00.000` (datetime) - Scheduled date of production, according to which the priority of tasks for issue to production will be set in the WMS. If the element is not filled in, the WMS sets the current day as the production date.
+ productionContractId: `1B28CDF0-C229-4192-ADD2-21FD715687F4` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the production contract.
+ priority: `50` (integer) – Priority of the production order.
+ note: `Note of the issue to production` (string(255)) - Note regarding the issue to production.

+ items.itemCode: `VP007024/001` (string (40)) - Unique identifier of the production order's item (might be arranged for example as "production order code/item code"). Each item code should be unique - if this cannot be ensured, it is necessary to use the element "items.extIsId".
+ items.extIsId: `648DC0FF` (string(1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP that must be used when it is not possible to ensure that the value in the element "items.itemCode" is unique. If the identification in the element "items.itemCode" is unique, "items.extIsId" should not be filled in.
+ items.productId: `AD0EFE39-EEF6-41AA-9ED5-E48E890A44B5` (string (1024), required) - Unique identifier of the product.
+ items.quantity: `50` (numeric (15,4), required) - Quantity of product in basic unit of measurement.
+ items.warehouseCode: `1` (string (20), required) - Warehouse code from the ERP.
+ items.locationCode: `LOC071031` (string (20)) - Location code from the WMS system to which the product is to be transferred (e.g. location in front of the machine).
+ items.commission: `C208211` (string (40)) - The commission code for which the product is issued to production.
+ items.batch: `LOT220217` (string (100)) - The production batch code which is to be issued to production.
+ items.batchExt: `LOT_2254` (string(20)) - Batch code recorded in the ERP.
+ items.expirationDate: `2023-09-24` (datetime) - Expiration date of the production batch.
+ items.variant: `VAR1` (string (100)) - Product variant code.
+ items.variantId: `DB2B98FC-0593-4676-9965-C91725E21D2E` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the variant.

+ parameters.paramCode: `ASPARAM658` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the production order's parameters. Each parameter code should be unique - if this cannot be ensured, it is necessary to use the element "parameters.extIsId".
+ parameters.extIsId: `594BD2VS` (string(1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP that must be used when it is not possible to ensure that the value in the element "parameters.paramCode" is unique. If the identification in the element "parameters.paramCode" is unique, "parameters.extIsId" should not be filled in.
+ parameters.productId: `DB2B98FC-0593-4676-9965-C91725E21D2E` (string (1024), required) - Unique identifier of the product.
+ parameters.amount: `5` (numeric (15,4), required) - Quantity of product in basic unit of measurement.
+ parameters.warehouseCode: `1` (string (20), required) - Warehouse code from the ERP.
+ parameters.variantId: `F539EAED-D281-4D27-BEE1-20BB563C71B8` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the variant.

### Create an Issue to production [POST /V1/issueToProduction/]

During the creation of an issue to production, the header is created along with all its items and parameters. Parameters are not required for the creation of an issue to production. If an error occurs during the creation of the issue to production, no value (neither header nor items) is inserted into the WMS database.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "productionOrderCode": "VP007024",
            "extIsId": "2ADEAC8D",
            "productionDate": "2022-05-21 14:50:00.000",
            "productionContractId": "1B28CDF0-C229-4192-ADD2-21FD715687F4",
            "priority": 50,
            "note": "Note of the issue to production",
            "items": [
                {
                    "itemCode": "VP007024/001",
                    "extIsId": "648DC0FF",
                    "productId": "AD0EFE39-EEF6-41AA-9ED5-E48E890A44B5",
                    "quantity": 50,
                    "warehouseCode": "1",
                    "locationCode": "LOC071031",
                    "commission": "C208211",
                    "batch": "LOT220217",
                    "batchExt": "LOT_2254",
                    "expirationDate": "2023-09-24",
                    "variantId": "DB2B98FC-0593-4676-9965-C91725E21D2E"
                }
            ],
            "parameters": [
                {
                    "paramCode": "ASPARAM658",
                    "extIsId": "594BD2VS",
                    "productId": "DB2B98FC-0593-4676-9965-C91725E21D2E",
                    "amount": 5,
                    "warehouseCode": "1",
                    "variantId": "F539EAED-D281-4D27-BEE1-20BB563C71B8"
                }
            ]
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
            "errors": [],
            "data": {
                "ids": [
                    {
                        "id": "2D47EC4F-55FC-48AA-9F40-582A3F791FDC",
                        "recordId": "0",
                        "sourceId": "2ADEAC8D",
                        "type": "issueToProduction"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "1887F0D6-190C-4BB7-B84D-BD6E6AB9363F",
                        "recordId": "1",
                        "sourceId": "648DC0FF",
                        "type": "issueToProductionItem"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "0C3DDF43-28E6-4DD3-9600-773BCC3B8D66",
                        "recordId": "1",
                        "sourceId": "594BD2VS",
