## Assembly [/V1/assembly/]
Base URI template that is used at the end of the URL when the web service is called: <b>/V1/assembly/</b> (example: https://demo.mystock.cz/V1/assembly/).

This web service is used when some product has to be assembled. Assembly represents any transformation of one or more source products into one or more target products (e.g. production of sets, repackaging, completion of the final product, etc.).

The web service has following elements: 
+ productionOrderCode: `AS007024` (string (20), required) - Production order code from the ERP system. Each production order code should be unique - if this cannot be ensured, it is necessary to use the element "extIsId".
+ extIsId: `8FWTAB6D` (string (1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP that must be used when it is not possible to ensure that the value in the element "productionOrderCode" is unique. If the identification in the element "productionOrderCode" is unique, "extIsId" should not be filled in.
+ productionDate: `2024-01-23 12:00:00.000` (datetime) - Scheduled date of production, according to which the priority of tasks for assembly will be set in the WMS. If the element is not filled in, the WMS sets the current day as the production date.
+ note: `Note of the assembly` (string(255)) - Note regarding the assembly.
+ priority: `50` (integer) – Priority of the production order.

+ items.itemCode: `AS007024/001` (string (40)) - Unique identifier of the production order's item (might be arranged for example as "production order code/item code"). Each item code should be unique - if this cannot be ensured, it is necessary to use the element "items.extIsId".
+ items.extIsId: `257BD8DS` (string(1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP that must be used when it is not possible to ensure that the value in the element "items.itemCode" is unique. If the identification in the element "items.itemCode" is unique, "items.extIsId" should not be filled in.
+ items.productId: `B050F4E2-1CC5-4DD1-8D87-FAE9155CF356` (string (1024), required) - Unique identifier of the product.
+ items.quantity: `50` (numeric (15,4), required) - Quantity of product in basic unit of measurement.
+ items.warehouseCode: `1` (string (20), required) - Warehouse code from the ERP.
+ items.locationCode: `LOC071031` (string (20)) - Location code from the WMS system to which the product is to be transferred (e.g. location in front of the machine).
+ items.commission: `C208211` (string (20)) - The commission code for which the product is assembled.
+ items.batch: `LOT220217` (string (100)) - The production batch code which is to be assembled.
+ items.batchExt: `LOT_2254` (string(20)) - Batch code recorded in the ERP.
+ items.expirationDate: `2024-09-24` (datetime) - Expiration date of the production batch.
+ items.minExpirationPeriod: `20` (smallint) - Minimum expiration period (in days) from the date of issue/shipment from the warehouse.
+ items.maxExpirationPeriod: `60` (smallint) - Maximum expiration period (in days) from the date of issue/shipment from the warehouse.
+ items.countryOfOriginId: `343659EE-58F8-4EC8-9AFF-4ACC713CA67B` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the country of origin.
+ items.variantId: `A3DD27A3-5400-4FCD-920D-68E34F853111` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the variant.

+ parameters.paramCode: `ASPARAM658` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the production order's parameter. Each parameter code should be unique - if this cannot be ensured, it is necessary to use the element "parameters.extIsId".
+ parameters.extIsId: `594BD2VS` (string(1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP that must be used when it is not possible to ensure that the value in the element "parameters.paramCode" is unique. If the identification in the element "parameters.paramCode" is unique, "parameters.extIsId" should not be filled in.
+ parameters.productId: `DB2B98FC-0593-4676-9965-C91725E21D2E` (string (1024), required) - Unique identifier of the product.
+ parameters.amount: `5` (numeric (15,4), required) - Quantity of product in basic unit of measurement.
+ parameters.warehouseCode: `1` (string (20), required) - Warehouse code from the ERP.
+ parameters.extProductCode: `PRPARAM254` (string (20)) – External product code.
+ parameters.commission: `D254185` (string (20)) - The commission code for which the product is assembled.
+ parameters.batch: `LOT548721` (string (100)) - The production batch code which is to be assembled.
+ parameters.batchExt: `LOT_225466` (string(20)) - Batch code recorded in the ERP.
+ parameters.expirationDate: `2024-06-10` (datetime) - Expiration date of the production batch.
+ parameters.countryOfOriginId: `343659EE-58F8-4EC8-9AFF-4ACC713CA67B` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the country of origin.
+ parameters.variantId: `F539EAED-D281-4D27-BEE1-20BB563C71B8` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the variant.

### Create an Assembly [POST /V1/assembly/]

During the creation of an assembly, the header is created along with all its items and parameters. If an error occurs during the creation of the assembly, no value (neither header nor items) is inserted into the WMS database.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "extIsId": "8FWTAB6D",
