## Production contract [/V1/productionContract/]
Base URI template that is used at the end of the URL when the web service is called: <b>/V1/productionContract/</b> (example: https://demo.mystock.cz/V1/productionContract/).

The web service has following elements: 
+ productionContractCode: `VZ254782` (string (20), required) - Production contract code from the ERP system. Each production contract code should be unique - if this cannot be ensured, it is necessary to use the element "extIsId".
+ extIsId: `2ADEAC8D` (string (1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP that must be used when it is not possible to ensure that the value in the element "productionContractCode" is unique. If the identification in the element "productionContractCode" is unique, "extIsId" should not be filled in.
+ priority: `50` (integer) – Priority of the production contract.

+ procedures.operationCode: `TP254145` (string (20), required) - Operation code from the ERP system. Each operation code should be unique - if this cannot be ensured, it is necessary to use the element "procedures.extIsId".
+ procedures.extIsId: `648DC0FF` (string(1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP that must be used when it is not possible to ensure that the value in the element "procedures.operationCode" is unique. If the identification in the element "procedures.operationCode" is unique, "procedures.extIsId" should not be filled in.
+ procedures.order: `1` (smallint, required) – Order of operation.
+ procedures.machineCenterCode: `SC1` (string (20), required) – Code of the machine center.
+ procedures.description: `Description of the operation` (varchar(max)) – Description of the operation.
+ procedures.execDate: `2024-02-02 12:00:00.000` (datetime) – Processing date and time (from).
+ procedures.partnerId: `63D7132B-3534-45B6-AD4F-5013FD505F35` (string(1024)) – Unique identifier of the partner - the ID is generated during the creation of the partner via API.

### Create a Production contract [POST /V1/productionContract/]
When a production contract is created, a production contract procedure can be created either alongside the production contract (see the section "procedures" in the example) or later with a separate service (see the header "Production contract procedure").
During the creation of a production contract, the header is created along with all its procedures. If an error occurs during the creation of the production contract, no value (neither header nor procedures) is inserted into the WMS database.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "productionContractCode": "VZ254782",
            "extIsId": "2ADEAC8D",
            "priority": 50,
            "procedures": [
                {
                    "operationCode": "TP254145",
                    "extIsId": "648DC0FF",
                    "order": 1,
                    "machineCenterCode": "SC1",
                    "description": "Description of the operation",
                    "execDate": "2024-02-02 12:00:00.000",
                    "partnerId": "63D7132B-3534-45B6-AD4F-5013FD505F35"
                }
            ]
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
            "errors": [],
            "data": {
                "ids": [
                    {
                        "id": "C3776241-5E21-4F56-9A4F-2887B70CD54C",
                        "recordId": "1",
                        "sourceId": "2ADEAC8D",
                        "type": "productionContract"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "F9E0726B-E527-4375-913B-6A5465CA9215",
                        "recordId": "0",
                        "sourceId": "648DC0FF",
                        "type": "productionContractProcedure"
                    }
                ]
            }
        }

+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
            "data": null,
            "errors": [
                {
                    "errorText": "Invalid entry",
                    "errorType": 3,
                    "internalRecordId": null,
                    "propertyName": "procedures.partnerId",
                    "recordId": "1",
                    "recordType": "productionContract",
                    "sourceId": "648DC0FF"
                }
            ]
        }

## Production contract procedure [/V1/productionContractProcedure/]
Base URI template that is used at the end of the URL when the web service is called: <b>/V1/productionContractProcedure/</b> (example: https://demo.mystock.cz/V1/productionContractProcedure/).

The web service has following elements: 
+ productionContractId: `70114862-7F91-4B19-AB36-3783DFCE2A07` (string (1024), required) - Unique identifier of the production contract - the ID is generated during the creation of the production contract via API.
+ operationCode: `TP254145` (string (20), required) - Operation code from the ERP system. Each operation code should be unique - if this cannot be ensured, it is necessary to use the element "extIsId".
+ extIsId: `648DC0FF` (string(1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP that must be used when it is not possible to ensure that the value in the element "operationCode" is unique. If the identification in the element "operationCode" is unique, "extIsId" should not be filled in.
+ order: `1` (smallint, required) – Order of operation.
+ machineCenterCode: `SC1` (string (20), required) – Code of the machine center.
+ description: `Description of the operation` (varchar(max)) – Description of the operation.
+ execDate: `2024-02-02 12:00:00.000` (datetime) – Processing date and time (from).
+ partnerId: `63D7132B-3534-45B6-AD4F-5013FD505F35` (string(1024)) – Unique identifier of the partner - the ID is generated during the creation of the partner via API.

### Create a Production contract procedure [POST /V1/productionContractProcedure/]
If an error occurs during the creation of the production contract procedure, no value is inserted into the WMS database.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "productionContractId": "70114862-7F91-4B19-AB36-3783DFCE2A07",
            "operationCode": "TP254145",
            "extIsId": "648DC0FF",
            "order": 1,
            "machineCenterCode": "SC1",
            "description": "Description of the operation",
            "execDate": "2024-02-02 12:00:00.000",
            "partnerId": "63D7132B-3534-45B6-AD4F-5013FD505F35"
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
            "errors": [],
            "data": {
                "ids": [
                    {
                        "id": "C918623B-3A11-4879-8679-F5CBAAC0D843",
                        "recordId": "1",
                        "sourceId": "648DC0FF",
                        "type": "productionContractProcedure"
                    }
                ]
            }
        }

+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
            "data": null,
            "errors": [
                {
                    "errorText": "Invalid entry",
                    "errorType": 3,
                    "internalRecordId": null,
                    "propertyName": "partnerId",
                    "recordId": "1",
                    "recordType": "productionContractProcedure",
                    "sourceId": "648DC0FF"
                }
            ]
        }

### Update a Production contract procedure [PUT /V1/productionContractProcedure/{productionContractProcedureId}]
In the update web service, it is always necessary to send a unique identification of the changed record (ID) in the URL. The body of the update web service should contain only those elements that need to be changed.

If one of the updated values is filled in incorrectly and the validation procedure reports an error, the system will cancel the whole update - none of the changed values will be updated.

List of elements that may be updated:
+ order: `1` (smallint) 
+ description: `Description of the operation` (varchar(max))
+ execDate: `2024-02-02 12:00:00.000` (datetime)
+ partnerId: `63D7132B-3534-45B6-AD4F-5013FD505F35` (string(1024))

+ Parameters
    + productionContractProcedureId: `AD74A5D7-BF54-456D-B910-8D549436B15D` (string) - A unique identifier of the production contract procedure you want to update.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "order": 1,
            "description": "Description of the operation",
            "execDate": "2024-02-02 12:00:00.000",
            "partnerId": "63D7132B-3534-45B6-AD4F-5013FD505F35"
        }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "errors": [],
            "data": "OK"
        }
        
+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
            "errors": [
                {
                    "errorType": 3,
                    "errorText": "Invalid entry",
                    "sourceId": "648DC0FF",
                    "recordId": "1",
                    "recordType": "productionContractProcedure",
                    "propertyName": "partnerId"
                }
            ],
            "data": null
        }

## Result of the initial inspection [/V1/resultOfTheInitialInspection/]

Base URI template that is used at the end of the URL when the web service is called: <b>/V1/resultOfTheInitialInspection/</b> (example: https://demo.mystock.cz/V1/resultOfTheInitialInspection/).

The web service has following elements:
+ extIsId: `E17C51BF` (string(1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP.
+ processingMethod: `10` (tinyint, required) - Method of processing the result. Supported values: 10 - Task creation (generation), 20 – Confirmation of a task already established in WMS
+ batchExt: `LOT_2254` (string(20), required) - Batch code recorded in the ERP.
+ quantity: `5` (numeric(15,4), required) - Quantity of product in the purchase unit of measurement (unless another unit of measurement is filled in).
+ measurementUnitCode: `KS` (string(1024), required) - Unit of measurement - code will be generated during the creation of unit of measurement in the WMS. If the element is not filled in, the WMS uses the basic unit of measurement for the product.
+ locationCode: `GARBAGE` (string(20), condition) - Destination location code. (location codes are defined in the WMS). Mandatory if the element "processImmediately" is 1, otherwise should not be filled in.
+ processImmediately: `1` (tinyint, required) - Process immediately (and finish). Supported values: 0 - No, 1 – Yes (element "locationCode" must also be filled in)). 

### Create a Result of the initial inspection [POST /V1/resultOfTheInitialInspection/]

During the creation of a result of the initial inspection, the header is created. If an error occurs during the creation of the result of the initial inspection, no value is inserted into the WMS database.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "extIsId": "E17C51BF",
            "processingMethod": 10,
            "batchExt": "LOT_2254",
            "quantity": 5,
            "measurementUnitCode": "KS",
            "locationCode": "GARBAGE",
            "processImmediately": 1
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
          "errors": [],
          "data": {
            "ids": [
              {
                "id": "722FA49D-8E3A-4A69-A1E5-F30843CF5FA1",
                "recordId": "1",
                "sourceId": "E17C51BF",
                "type": "resultOfTheInitialInspection"
              }
            ]
          }
        }
       
+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
            "data": null,
            "errors": [
                {
                    "errorText": "Invalid entry",
                    "errorType": 3,
                    "internalRecordId": null,
                    "propertyName": "measurementUnitCode",
                    "recordId": "1",
                    "recordType": "resultOfTheInitialInspection",
                    "sourceId": "E17C51BF"
                }
            ]
        }

## Inventory check [/V1/inventoryCheck/]

Base URI template that is used at the end of the URL when the web service is called: <b>/V1/inventoryCheck/</b> (example: https://demo.mystock.cz/V1/inventoryCheck/).

The web service has following elements:
+ inventoryCode: `INV00024` (string (20), required) - Code of the inventory check from the ERP system. Each code of the inventory check should be unique - if this cannot be ensured, it is necessary to use the element "extIsId".
+ extIsId: `0AC9D323` (string(1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the record in the ERP that must be used when it is not possible to ensure that the value in the element "inventoryCode" is unique. If the identification in the element "inventoryCode" is unique, "extIsId" should not be filled in.
+ warehouseCode: `1` (string (20), required) - Warehouse code from the ERP for which you want to do an inventory check.
+ sectionCode: `AUTOSTORE` (string (1024)) - Code of the warehouse section is generated when the section is created in the mySTOCK WMS. Section creation is not imported via API.
+ startingDate: `2022-12-20 00:00:00.000` (datetime) - Scheduled starting date of the inventory check.
+ note: `Text including notes for the given inventory check` (string (32766)) - Note regarding the inventory check, this note is displayed in the server part of the WMS.
+ fullWarehouseInventory: `0` (tinyint) - Determining whether it is a full inventory of all external IS warehouses. Supported values: 0 - No, 1 – Yes (then none of the elements sectionCode or the items collection may be filled in.)
+ commissionStockRestriction: `0` (tinyint) - The setting defines inventory restrictions on stock items based on the value of the commission attribute. Supported values: 0 - All, 10 - Stock only, 20 - Commission only

+ items.productId: `A8BE340A-564C-4464-B554-24EE280C5537` (string (1024)) - If you want to do an inventory check for one or more specific products, you can fill in identification of those products - inventory check will then be done only for those products. If no product is filled in, the inventory check applies to all products registered under the given warehouse.

### Create an Inventory check [POST /V1/inventoryCheck/]

During the creation of an inventory check, the inventory check header is created along with all its items, if they are filled in. If an error occurs during the creation of the inventory check, no value (neither header nor items) is inserted into the WMS database.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
        "inventoryCode": "INV00024",
        "extIsId": "0AC9D323",
        "warehouseCode": "1",
        "sectionCode": "AUTOSTORE",
        "startingDate": "2022-12-20 00:00:00.000",
        "note": "Text including notes for the given inventory check",
        "fullWarehouseInventory": 0,
        "commissionStockRestriction": 0,
        "items": [
            {
            "productId": "A8BE340A-564C-4464-B554-24EE280C5537"
            }
            ]
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
            "errors": [],
            "data": {
                "ids": [
                    {
                        "id": "47834C09-56C2-4799-9965-F235F8548E74",
                        "recordId": "1",
                        "sourceId": "0AC9D323",
                        "type": "inventoryCheck"
                    }
                ]
            }
        }
        
+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
        "data": null,
        "errors": [
            {
                "errorText": "Invalid value",
                "errorType": 3,
                "internalRecordId": null,
                "propertyName": "warehouseCode",
                "recordId": "1",
                "recordType": "inventoryCheck",
                "sourceId": "0AC9D323"
            }
            ]
        }

## Inventory check results [/V1/inventoryCheckResult/]

Base URI template that is used at the end of the URL when the web service is called: <b>/V1/inventoryCheckResult/</b> (example: https://demo.mystock.cz/V1/inventoryCheckResult/).

The web service has following parameters:
+ inventoryId: `45790E69-2EED-4D10-8DA7-E25C2486F4BC` (string (1024), required) - Unique identifier of the inventory check.
+ recordsPerPage: `1000` (numeric (15,4), optional) - Number of records per page that will be returned as a result of the web service. The allowed range is from 10 to 1000 records - if the parameter is not specified, the web service automatically returns 1000 recorde per page.
+ page: `1` (numeric (15,4), optional) - Results page number (results are sent according to the set number of records per page). If the parameter is not specified, the web service automatically returns the first page of results.

### Get Inventory check results [GET /V1/inventoryCheckResult/{inventoryId}{?recordsPerPage}{?page}]
Inventory check results web service is used to display the results of the inventory check that was finished in the WMS. When the results of the inventory check are exported, the WMS sends event 25.

Each displayed result has following elements:
+ productId: `2EF4324F-0FFF-4941-A257-DC89DE98FA07` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the product.
+ quantity: `20` (numeric (15,4)) - Counted quantity of the inventory item (product) in the basic unit of measurement. The quantity of the product is always recorded for specific attributes (location, batch, quality, ...).
+ measurementUnitCode: `KS` (string (1024)) - Basic unit of measurement of the product.
+ erpWarehouseCode: `U0001` (string (20)) - Code of the particular ERP warehouse under which the product is being stored.
+ location: `AVAILABLE` (string (20)) - WMS location code, usually only two locations are used: available and unavailable (location codes are defined in the WMS).
+ commission: `AP90T` (string (20)) - Commission number of the product (filled in only if the product was manufactured/received for certain commission and if the attribute "commission" is switched on in the WMS).
+ batch: `LOT220110` (string (100)) - Batch number of the product (filled in only if the product has batch registration enabled in the WMS).
+ batchExt: `LOT_2254` (string(20)) - Batch code recorded in the ERP.
+ expirationDate: `2023-10-05 00:00:00.000` (datetime) - Expiration date of the product.
+ variant: `VAR1` (string (100)) - Product variant code (filled in only if the product has variant registration enabled in the WMS).
+ exportDate: `2022-01-20 15:14:07.580` (datetime) - Date and time when the inventory check results were exported from the WMS.

+ Parameters
    + inventoryId: `45790E69-2EED-4D10-8DA7-E25C2486F4BC` (string, required) - Unique identifier of the inventory check.
    + recordsPerPage: `1000` (numeric, optional) - Number of records per page that should be returned as a result of the web service. The allowed range is from 10 to 1000 records.
    + page: `1` (numeric, optional) - Results page number (results are sent according to the set number of records per page).

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
        "data": 
            {
            "count": 2,
            "result": [
                {
                "productId": "2EF4324F-0FFF-4941-A257-DC89DE98FA07",
                "quantity": 20,
                "measurementUnitCode": "KS",
                "erpWarehouseCode": "U0001",
                "location": "AVAILABLE",
                "commission": "AP90T",
                "batch": "LOT220110",
                "batchExt": "LOT_2254",
                "expirationDate": "2023-10-05 00:00:00.000",
                "variant": "VAR1",
                "exportDate": "2022-01-20 15:14:07.580"
                },
                {
                "productId": "F834F975-0B9A-49C3-9694-027F49B18AA8",
                "quantity": 125,
                "measurementUnitCode": "KS",
                "erpWarehouseCode": "U0001",
                "location": "AVAILABLE",
                "commission": null,
                "batch": null,
                "expirationDate": null,
                "variant": "VAR1",
                "exportDate": "2022-01-20 15:14:07.580"
                }
            ]
        },
        "errors": []
        }

## Inventory price request [/V1/inventoryPriceRequest/]

Base URI template that is used at the end of the URL when the web service is called: <b>/V1/inventoryPriceRequest/</b> (example: https://demo.mystock.cz/V1/inventoryPriceRequest/).

The web service has following parameters:
+ inventoryId: `45790E69-2EED-4D10-8DA7-E25C2486F4BC` (string (1024), required) - Unique identifier of the inventory check.
+ recordsPerPage: `1000` (numeric (15,4), optional) - Number of records per page that will be returned as a result of the web service. The allowed range is from 10 to 1000 records - if the parameter is not specified, the web service automatically returns 1000 recorde per page.
+ page: `1` (numeric (15,4), optional) - Results page number (results are sent according to the set number of records per page). If the parameter is not specified, the web service automatically returns the first page of results.

### Get Inventory price request [GET /V1/inventoryPriceRequest/{inventoryId}{?recordsPerPage}{?page}]
Inventory price request web service is used to display the list of items of the inventory check that need to be valued. When the inventory price request is exported, the WMS sends event 33.

Each displayed result has following elements:
+ batch: `LOT220110` (string (100)) - Batch number of the product (filled in only if the product has batch registration enabled in the WMS).
+ batchExt: `LOT_2254` (string(20)) - Batch code recorded in the ERP.
+ commission: `AP90T` (string (20)) - Commission number of the product (filled in only if the product was manufactured/received for certain commission and if the attribute "commission" is switched on in the WMS).
+ countryOfOriginId: `CZ` (string(1024)) - Country of origin code.
+ currency: `CZK` (string (3)) - Code of currency.
+ erpWarehouseCode: `U0001` (string (20)) - Code of the particular ERP warehouse under which the product is being stored.
+ expirationDate: `2028-10-05 00:00:00.000` (datetime) - Expiration date of the product.
+ exportDate: `2025-05-20 15:14:07.580` (datetime) - Date and time when the inventory price request was exported from the WMS.
+ inventoryId: `45790E69-2EED-4D10-8DA7-E25C2486F4BC` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the inventory check.
+ productId: `3DE84BF8-86CB-4600-9B82-DE42DBD2AF03` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the product.
+ qualityId: `DCE838E1-5A27-48EF-9746-7E1C62791776` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the quality. A property of the stock card that defines the level of its quality. (filled in only if the quality is being recorded and the attribute "quality" is switched on in the WMS)
+ variant: `VAR1` (string (100)) - Product variant code (filled in only if the product has variant registration enabled in the WMS).

+ Parameters
    + inventoryId: `45790E69-2EED-4D10-8DA7-E25C2486F4BC` (string, required) - Unique identifier of the inventory check.
    + recordsPerPage: `1000` (numeric, optional) - Number of records per page that should be returned as a result of the web service. The allowed range is from 10 to 1000 records.
    + page: `1` (numeric, optional) - Results page number (results are sent according to the set number of records per page).

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "errors": [],
            "data": {
                "count": 2,
                "result": [
                    {
                        "batch": "LOT220110",
                        "batchExt": "LOT_2254",
                        "commission": "AP90T",
                        "countryOfOriginId": "CZ",
                        "currency": "CZK",
                        "erpWarehouseCode": "U0001",
                        "expirationDate": "2028-10-05 00:00:00.000",
                        "exportDate": "2025-05-20 15:14:07.580",
                        "inventoryId": "45790E69-2EED-4D10-8DA7-E25C2486F4BC",
                        "productId": "3DE84BF8-86CB-4600-9B82-DE42DBD2AF03",
                        "qualityId": "DCE838E1-5A27-48EF-9746-7E1C62791776",
                        "variant": "VAR1"
                    },
                    {
                        "batch": null,
                        "batchExt": null,
                        "commission": null,
                        "countryOfOriginId": "SK",
                        "currency": "EUR",
                        "erpWarehouseCode": "U0001",
                        "expirationDate": null,
                        "exportDate": "2025-05-20 15:14:07.580",
                        "inventoryId": "45790E69-2EED-4D10-8DA7-E25C2486F4BC",
                        "productId": "F7BDD360-920F-4FDC-A454-4469AB5A0CC7",
                        "qualityId": null,
                        "variant": "VAR2"
                    }
                ]
            }
        }

## Inventory items price [/V1/inventoryItemsPrice/]

Base URI template that is used at the end of the URL when the web service is called: <b>/V1/inventoryItemsPrice/</b> (example: https://demo.mystock.cz/V1/inventoryItemsPrice/).

### Update an Inventory items price [PUT /V1/inventoryItemsPrice/{inventoryId}]
In the update web service, it is always necessary to send a unique identification of the changed record (ID) in the URL. The body of the update web service should contain only those elements that need to be changed.

If one of the updated values is filled in incorrectly and the validation procedure reports an error, the system will cancel the whole update - none of the changed values will be updated.

List of elements that may be updated:
+ items.batch: `LOT220110` (string (100), condition) - Batch number of the product (filled in only if the product has batch registration enabled in the WMS).
+ items.batchExt: `LOT_2254` (string(20)) - Batch code recorded in the ERP.
+ items.commission: `AP90T` (string (20), condition) - Commission number of the product (filled in only if the product was manufactured/received for certain commission and if the attribute "commission" is switched on in the WMS).
+ items.countryOfOriginId: `CZ` (string(1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the country of origin.
+ items.currency: `CZK` (string (3)) - Code of currency.
+ items.erpWarehouseCode: `U0001` (string (20), required) - Code of the particular ERP warehouse under which the product is being stored.
+ items.expirationDate: `2028-10-05 00:00:00.000` (datetime, condition) - Expiration date of the product.
+ items.productId: `3DE84BF8-86CB-4600-9B82-DE42DBD2AF03` (string (1024), required) - Unique identifier of the product.
+ items.qualityId: `DCE838E1-5A27-48EF-9746-7E1C62791776` (string (1024), condition) - Unique identifier of the quality. A property of the stock card that defines the level of its quality. (filled in only if the quality is being recorded and the attribute "quality" is switched on in the WMS)
+ items.variant: `VAR1` (string (100), condition) - Product variant code (filled in only if the product has variant registration enabled in the WMS).
+ items.price: `200` (numeric (16,5), required) - Item price.

+ Parameters
    + inventoryId: `45790E69-2EED-4D10-8DA7-E25C2486F4BC` (string, required) - Unique identifier of the inventory check.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "items": [
                {
                    "batch": "LOT220110",
                    "batchExt": "LOT_2254",
                    "commission": "AP90T",
                    "countryOfOriginId": "CZ",
                    "currency": "CZK",
                    "erpWarehouseCode": "U0001",
                    "expirationDate": "2028-10-05 00:00:00.000",
                    "productId": "3DE84BF8-86CB-4600-9B82-DE42DBD2AF03",
                    "qualityId": "DCE838E1-5A27-48EF-9746-7E1C62791776",
                    "variant": "VAR1",
                    "price": 200
                },
                {
                    "batch": null,
                    "batchExt": null,
                    "commission": null,
                    "countryOfOriginId": "SK",
                    "currency": "EUR",
                    "erpWarehouseCode": "U0001",
                    "expirationDate": null,
                    "productId": "F7BDD360-920F-4FDC-A454-4469AB5A0CC7",
                    "qualityId": null,
                    "variant": "VAR2",
                    "price": 10.50
                }
            ]
        }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
        "data": "OK",
        "errors": []
        }
        
+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
            "errors": [
                {
                    "errorType": 4,
                    "errorText": "The expiration date of product must be filled in, expiration date is mandatory for the product.",
                    "sourceId": "3DE84BF8-86CB-4600-9B82-DE42DBD2AF03",
                    "recordId": "1",
                    "recordType": "InventoryItemsPrice",
                    "propertyName": "items.expirationDate"
                }
            ],
            "data": null
        }

## Stock card [/V1/stockCard/]

Base URI template that is used at the end of the URL when the web service is called: <b>/V1/stockCard/</b> (example: https://demo.mystock.cz/V1/stockCard/).

The web service has following parameters:
+ erpWarehouseCode: `WH1` (string (20)) - Code of the particular ERP warehouse for which you want to display stock cards from the WMS. The parameter is not mandatory, and if it is not filled in, the WMS will display all stock cards for the given ERP system.

### Get stock cards for warehouse [GET /V1/stockCard/{erpWarehouseCode}/]

Stock card web service is used to display non-zero stock cards registered in the WMS for a given ERP system. Due to increased system requirements, stock cards are exported from the WMS at regular intervals (e.g. once a day at night - the stock card export interval is set in the WMS), which means that the moment of calling the web service is not the same as the moment when the stock cards were exported from the WMS.

The displayed stock cards have information about the date and time of their export: The export adds new items, updates records with quantity changes, retains records without any quantity changes, and removes items that have been zeroed out. The exportDate element is set to the time of the new export for added and updated records, and remains unchanged for retained (unchanged) records.

Each displayed stock card has following elements:
+ productId: `A770B14D-9E31-427C-9B19-A3D79D3BE8F9` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the product.
+ quantityTotal: `137` (numeric (15,4)) - Total quantity of the stored product in the basic unit of measurement. The total quantity of the product is always recorded for specific attributes (location, batch, quality, ...).
+ erpWarehouseCode: `U0001` (string (20)) - Code of the particular ERP warehouse under which the product is being stored.
+ location: `AVAILABLE` (string (20)) - WMS location code, usually only two locations are used: available and unavailable (location codes are defined in the WMS).
+ batch: `LOT211007` (string (100)) - Batch number of the product (filled in only if the product has batch registration enabled in the WMS).
+ batchExt: `LOT_2254` (string(20)) - Batch code recorded in the ERP.
+ expirationDate: `2022-09-24 00:00:00.000` (datetime) - Expiration date of the product.
+ countryOfOrigin: `CZ` (string(3)) - Country of origin code.
+ countryOfOriginId: `343659EE-58F8-4EC8-9AFF-4ACC713CA67B` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the country of origin.
+ commission: `9ZTGNP` (string (20)) - Commission number of the product (filled in only if the product was manufactured/received for certain commission and if the attribute "commission" is switched on in the WMS).
+ exportDate: `2021-10-19 11:41:13.130` (datetime) - Date and time when the stock cards were exported from the WMS.
+ quality: `1` (string (20)) - Quality of the product (filled in only if the quality is being recorded and the attribute "quality" is switched on in the WMS).


+ Parameters
    + erpWarehouseCode: `U0001` (optional) - A unique code of the ERP warehouse.

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
        "data": 
            {
            "count": 3,
            "result": [
                {
                "productId": "5E4E04CE-2E55-4778-A889-13072DD321AD",
                "quantityTotal": 137,
                "erpWarehouseCode": "U0001",
                "location": "AVAILABLE",
                "batch": null,
                "batchExt": "LOT_2254",
                "expirationDate": null,
                "countryOfOriginId": "343659EE-58F8-4EC8-9AFF-4ACC713CA67B",
                "commission": null,
                "exportDate": "2021-10-19 11:41:13.130",
                "quality": null
                },
                {
                "productId": "707DE505-DCD8-48A2-9F03-68BD8D29A4DD",
                "quantityTotal": 25,
                "erpWarehouseCode": "U0001",
                "location": "AVAILABLE",
                "batch": null,
                "expirationDate": null,
                "countryOfOriginId": null,
                "commission": null,
                "exportDate": "2021-10-19 11:41:13.130",
                "quality": null
                },
                {
                "productId": "85BB891F-9AD8-4509-BD35-F77CE829BB27",
                "quantityTotal": 49,
                "erpWarehouseCode": "U0001",
                "location": "UNAVAILABLE",
                "batch": null,
                "expirationDate": null,
                "countryOfOriginId": null,
                "commission": null,
                "exportDate": "2021-10-19 11:41:13.130",
                "quality": null
                }
            ]
        },
        "errors": []
        }

## Product stock card [/V1/productStockCard/]

Base URI template that is used at the end of the URL when the web service is called: <b>/V1/productStockCard/</b> (example: https://demo.mystock.cz/V1/productStockCard/).

The web service has following parameters:
+ productId: `5E4E04CE-2E55-4778-A889-13072DD321AD` (string, required) - Unique identifier of the product.
+ erpWarehouseCode: `U0001` (string) - Code of the particular ERP warehouse for which you want to display product's stock cards from the WMS. The parameter is not mandatory, and if it is not filled in, the WMS will display all stock cards for the given product regardless of the ERP warehouse.

### Get stock cards for product [GET /V1/productStockCard/{productId}{?erpWarehouseCode}]

This web service is used to display non-zero stock cards registered in the WMS for a given product. Displayed stock cards for the product are exported from the WMS when the web service is called, which means that the stock cards should be up to date, but there still might be a slight delay between the moment when the web service is used and the moment when the results are displayed (during this time period stock cards in the WMS might still change due to ongoing processes in the warehouse).

Each displayed stock card has following elements:
+ quantityTotal: `137` (numeric (15,4)) - Total quantity of the stored product in the basic unit of measurement. The total quantity of the product is always recorded for specific attributes (location, batch, quality, ...).
+ erpWarehouseCode: `U0001` (string (20)) - Code of the particular ERP warehouse under which the product is being stored.
+ location: `AVAILABLE` (string (20)) - WMS location code, usually only two locations are used: available and unavailable (location codes are defined in the WMS).
+ batch: `LOT211007` (string (100)) - Batch number of the product (filled in only if the product has batch registration enabled in the WMS).
+ batchExt: `LOT_2254` (string(20)) - Batch code recorded in the ERP.
+ expirationDate: `2022-09-24 00:00:00.000` (datetime) - Expiration date of the product.
+ commission: `9ZTGNP` (string (20)) - Commission number of the product (filled in only if the product was manufactured/received for certain commission and the attribute "commission" is switched on in the WMS).
+ quality: `1` (string (20)) - Quality of the product (filled in only if the quality is being recorded and the attribute "quality" is switched on in the WMS).


+ Parameters
    + productId: `5E4E04CE-2E55-4778-A889-13072DD321AD` (required) - Unique identifier of the product.
    + erpWarehouseCode: `U0001` (optional) - A unique code of the ERP warehouse.


+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
        "data": 
            {
            "count": 1,
            "result": [
                {
                "quantityTotal": 137,
                "erpWarehouseCode": "U0001",
                "location": "AVAILABLE",
                "batch": null,
                "batchExt": "LOT_2254",
                "expirationDate": null,
                "commission": null,
                "quality": null
                }
            ]
        },
        "errors": []
        }

## Exporting mySTOCK events [/V1/event]

List of all possible mySTOCK event elements: 61
+ atestDate: `2022-07-25 00:00:00.000` (datetime) - Date of atest.
+ atestNumber: `2022/199241` (string(20)) - Internal atest number.
+ barcode: `0410000000113` (string (30)) - Scanned product barcode in process on PDA. 
+ batch: `LOT220217` (string(100)) - The production batch code of the product. Filled in only if the attribute "batch" is switched on in the WMS.
+ batchExt: `LOT_2254` (string(20)) - Batch code recorded in the ERP.
+ commission: `C208211` (string(20)) - The commission code of the product. Filled in only if the attribute "commission" is switched on in the WMS.
+ commissionTo: `C352123` (string(20)) - The target commission code of the product. Filled in only if the attribute "commission" is switched on in the WMS.
+ deliveryMethodId: `PPL` (string (1024)) - Identification of the delivery method - the identification is generated during the creation of the delivery method in the WMS.
+ depth: `0.2` (numeric (8,4)) - Depth of logistics unit (m).
+ documentCode: `23642203153` (string (20)) - Number of the document´s (Receipt/Order incoming) header.
+ documentId: `A4C085B6-C704-4BFF-8384-B9919B282FB8`(string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the document's (Receipt/Order incoming/Loading document) header.
+ documentType: `Receipt` (string(255)) - Type of the document´s header. For event 3 - for example: Receipt, OrderIncoming etc.
+ documentWms: `VD_45422` (string(100)) - Number of the document´s header from WMS. For event 5 - issue.
+ eventId: `2949C3DE-F4AC-4FF7-8AF8-48EBED3EA7A6` (guid) - Unique event ID.
+ eventSubtype: `3` (tinyint) - Reported subtype of the event, some types of events support multiple subtypes, in this case it is always necessary to select which action (subtype number) is reported by the event.
+ eventTime: `2021-09-30 12:31:12.195` (datetime) - Information about the date and time when the event occured in the WMS. If an error occurs during the creation of the event, the event is sent again and information about the date and time will be updated.
+ eventType: `20` (tinyint) - Type of reported event, each event has a unique designation (number).
+ expirationDate: `2023-09-24 00:00:00.000` (datetime) - Expiration date of the production batch. Filled in only if the attribute "batch" is switched on in the WMS.
+ externalStatusId: `50` (string (1024)) - Aggregated status of the shipment.
+ fullTrackingNumber: `%00747312377000011101203` (string (255)) - Full tracking number of the shipment. If there are multiple full tracking numbers for the same shipment, the full tracking numbers are separated in collection "trackingNumbers" by a comma. For Event 12 filled in only for subtype 1.
+ height: `0.2` (numeric (8,4)) - Height of logistics unit (m).
+ items: `0.001` (numeric (15,4)) - Calculated volume (m3) .
+ itemId: `DD19A0A8-28E1-435C-B86B-479D601A7237` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the document's item.
+ itemType: `ReceiptItem` (string(255)) - Type of the document´s item. For event 3 - for example: ReceiptItem, OrderIncomingItem etc.
+ loadingId: `9573024C-D3F8-4FB8-A588-CC9E72D4E4CF` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the loading document.
+ loadingMeter: `0.011` (numeric (8,4)) - Loading area (LDM) of the logistics unit.
+ locationCode: `DISP` (string (20)) - Location code from the ERP system.
+ locationFrom: `AVAILABLE` (string (20)) - Default location code (for the purpose of reporting from the WMS to the ERP, usually only two locations are used: available and unavailable - location codes are defined in the WMS).
+ locationTo: `UNAVAILABLE` (string (20)) - Destination location code (for the purpose of reporting from the WMS to the ERP, usually only two locations are used: available and unavailable - location codes are defined in the WMS).
+ logisticLabelCode: `Z21241242` (string(20)) - Code of the logistic label in which the item was exported.
+ logisticUnit: `0.008` (numeric (15,4)) - Specified volume (m3).
+ logisticUnitCode: `ESHOP0000026327` (string (20)) - Logistic unit code - this is how the logistic unit is identified in the warehouse until the shipping label is added. The ERP must return this code in the "logisticUnitCode" element when importing shipping labels (see the Shipping label web service).
+ logisticUnitId: `55BD4851-8278-4C85-861E-E88AAA61B6D9` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the logistic unit.
+ logisticUnitLabel: `NK00231459` (string(20)) - Code of the logistic unit in which the item was imported.
+ logisticUnitStatus: `new` (tinyint) - Status of the logistic unit. Supported values: new, recalculate, ok.
+ measurementUnitCode: `KS` (string (1024)) - Unit of measurement in which the product in the logistics unit is issued - the code is generated during the creation of unit of measurement in the WMS. For Event 28 - The unit of measure of the pending item (product) of the document - the code is generated when the unit of measure is created in the WMS.
+ note: `Packet is on the way from branch 567 to branch 4456.` (string (32766)) - Additional information used for specific events.
+ packageCode: `N000000876` (string (20)) - Code of the received carrier (package/transport package/returnable package). 
+ packageType: `EURO` (string (20)) - Type of the recieved transport package.
+ packagingTypeCode: `EUR` (string (20)) – Code of the carrier’s packaging type (e.g. EUR for a Europallet) – some carriers require this information.
+ printerCode: `PRIJEM01` (string(60)) - The code of the printer to which the print is to be sent.
+ printLanguage: `CZ` (string(20)) - Language code of the printed document (if there are any variations).
+ printType: `T1` (string(20)) - Type of the print (if there are any variations).
+ productCode: `100160984-BAS-BA-0-XXL` (string (150)) - Unique product code from the ERP.
+ productId: `7100A908-23D0-4903-804A-80A3AD1DE104` (string (1024)) - Unique identifier of the product.
+ productName: `SPT ML NI STRETCH PINPOINT SOLID MILANO SODALITE` (string (255)) - Product name.
+ quantity: `10.1234` (numeric (15,4)) - The amount of product in the basic unit of measurement for which the event is reported. For Event 28 - Quantity of pending document item (product) by reason.
+ quantityOfItem: `5` (numeric (15,4)) - The amount of item in the logistic unit in the product’s basic unit of measurement.
+ serialNumber: `11084` (string(40)) - Serial number.
+ serialShippingContainerCode: `120000000000000340` (string (20)) - SSCC code of the logistics unit.
+ shippingLabel: `DR2082000056C` (string (32766)) - Shipping label code. If there are multiple shipping labels for the same order incoming, the shipping labels are separated by a comma.
+ shipmentPairingCode: `C327` (string (20)) - A pairing code that is used to merge several orders incoming together.
+ status: `OK` (string (3)) - Informs whether the weight check passed within the defined tolerance (OK/NOK). For Event 26 filled in only for subtype 2.
+ transportOperator: `Zásilkovna` (string (20)) - Identification of the transport operator that delivers the shipping label.
+ variant: `A/03C` (string (100)) - Product variant code (filled in only if the product has variant registration enabled in the WMS).
+ volume: `0.035` (numeric (17,6)) - Volume of the product (m3).
+ warehouseCode: `1` (string (20)) - Warehouse code from the ERP.
+ warehouseCodeErpFrom: `10` (string (20)) - ERP default warehouse code. For Event 19 filled in only for subtype 2.
+ warehouseCodeErpTo: `20` (string (20)) - ERP destination warehouse code. For Event 19 filled in only for subtype 1.
+ warehouseCodeWmsFrom: `1001` (string (20)) - WMS default warehouse code.
+ warehouseCodeWmsTo: `1002` (string (20)) - WMS destination warehouse code. For Event 19 filled in only for subtype 1.
+ weightGross: `3` (numeric (18,7)) - Weight of the logistics unit (kg).
+ weightRecorded: `1,3250000` (numeric (18,7)) - Measured weight of the logistic unit (including its contents). For Event 26 filled in only for subtype 2.
+ width: `0.2` (numeric (8,4)) - Width of logistics unit (m).

### Event 1 - Request to print from the ERP system [POST]
<b>Event 1</b> sends a request for printing a label or a document from the ERP system. Supported event subtypes:
+ 1 - Product barcode
+ 2 - Delivery note
+ 3 - Invoice
+ 4 - Product label
+ 5 - Production guide
+ 6 - Certificate
+ 7 - Expedition label
+ 8 - Packing list

The processing of an event on the external information system side is not conditioned by the processing of an event of another type.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
        "eventId": "F0BBA044-63D2-42EF-A642-421EC70C3E76",
        "eventType": 1,
        "eventSubtype": 1,
        "documentId": null,
        "itemId": null,
        "productId": "6A6F9837-B9AB-4C61-AF23-F6024C36A040",
        "quantity": 2,
        "batch": null,
        "expirationDate": null,
        "commission": null,
        "printerCode": "PRIJEM01",
        "printLanguage": "CZ",
        "printType": null
        }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
        "data": 
            {
                "id": "erpId_76352839201"
            },
        "errors": []
        }
        
+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
        "data": null,
        "errors": [
            {
                "errorText": "Unable to process event"
            }
            ]
        }

### Event 2 - Request to print shipping label from the ERP system [POST]

<b>Event 2</b> sends a request for printing a shipping label for a single logistics unit or the entire shipment (more than one logistics unit). The event is linked to the order incoming.
Supported event subtypes:
+ 1 - Request to print shipping labels for the whole order incoming (input is the order incoming ID; the ERP must respond by sending all shipping labels for the given order incoming to the printer).
+ 2 - Request to print shipping label for a single logistics unit (input is the ID/code of the logistics unit linked to the order incoming; the ERP must respond by sending one shipping label for the given logstics unit to the printer).

The processing of an event on the external information system side is conditioned on processing events for the same document in the order in which they were created.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "eventType": 2,
            "eventSubtype": 1,
            "eventTime": "2025-09-24 10:50:34.077",
