### Event 3 - Change of location or warehouse of the ERP system (caused by the change of location in the WMS) [POST]
<b>Event 3</b> informs about a change of location or about a change of ERP warehouse within the WMS (WMS works with only 2 locations for the needs of communication with ERP: available and unavailable - location codes are defined in the WMS). Supported event subtypes:
+ 1 - Change of location or change of ERP warehouse or change of WMS warehouse (no longer used)
+ 2 - Movement in external warehouse according to the movement queue (no longer used)
+ 3 - Change of external location or external warehouse according to the movement queue

The processing of an event on the external information system side is conditioned by the processing of an event of the same type for the same product and the same WMS warehouse.

Recommendation:
<br>Upon receiving the event, it is recommended to cancel opposite movements.</br>
<br>For events that cannot be processed, repeat the event when increasing the quantity or canceling the blockage.</br>

