### Event 34 – Insufficient Quantity for Allocation [POST] 
<b>Event 34</b> informs about the quantity of items of the order incoming that could not be allocated in the WMS. The event is generated shortly after the order incoming is imported into the WMS.
The external information system evaluates this event and sends an update of the document (e.g., reduces the quantity of items that could not be allocated, cancels the order incoming, updates the cash-on-delivery amount, etc.).

The processing of an event on the external information system side is not conditioned by the processing of an event of another type.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "eventType": 34,
            "eventTime": "2025-12-02 10:24:47.740",
            "eventId": "47FF902A-2BC9-F011-95ED-00155D3A6A05",
